	quest.011FF0DB30456252.quest_desc: [
		"Pastel is a full-feature magic mod centered around the exploration of color as resonance, as natural energy. It is a long, expansive journey through the path of the artist that sees you not just learning, but discovering more about the land; explore the world and see it grow alongside you and see things that were not there before. "
		""
		"Pursue the meaning of the rainbow, of nature, and create new and powerful tools as your newfound comprehension allows you to make yet finer works. Make striking machines and from them assemble contraptions fit to support your march towards the heart of magic. "
		""
		""
		"And once you begin to believe you understand the lands and their essence, descend past the earth's false floor."
	]
	quest.011FF0DB30456252.quest_subtitle: "Colorful World"
	quest.011FF0DB30456252.title: "Pastel"
	quest.0160E410BBBA98DC.title: "Respawn the Dragon"
	quest.01BE056033288CCE.quest_desc: ["Visit &l&9Chapter Two: Putting Down Roots&r&r for food and farming challenges! Its a ludractive way to start earning money."]
	quest.01BE056033288CCE.title: "Expanding the Homestead"
	quest.024F55CAFFBC4BE7.quest_desc: ["The Shortblade can be used in off handed attacks and in crafting to cut materials."]
	quest.026682BD379CF002.quest_desc: ["Your first metal hammer! Time to get to some true smithing!"]
	quest.026682BD379CF002.title: "Iron Hammer: Tier III"
	quest.028BAD294AD040AF.quest_subtitle: "Discover a Catacomb"
	quest.02E1C18734A64F61.quest_desc: ["Combine runes to craft the Rainbow Rune"]
	quest.031375BDCC05EE98.quest_subtitle: "One of the important components for your Airship"
	quest.031375BDCC05EE98.title: "Airship Engine"
	quest.03791893E13743DF.quest_subtitle: "Gym Ticket for Players"
	quest.038F3D779491310A.title: "Shifting Blade"
	quest.03B0A30D83A54DEF.title: "Rage Quit"
	quest.03FFC76D89BE5D29.quest_desc: ["The Sickle head will allow you to break plant blocks in a wide area."]
	quest.046BD3375C2B06BE.quest_desc: ["Can be locked or set to trusted. Can also have items piped in and out via Logistical Transporter"]
	quest.04901DB2A0FD39E2.quest_subtitle: "Fluid Transport"
	quest.04FC98FCA731C4A9.quest_desc: ["Some Rod and Book Items like Sticks, Blaze Rods, and Prismarine Rods can be placed as blocks into the world. Search \"Placeable\" in JEI to see which items can be placed as blocks."]
	quest.04FC98FCA731C4A9.title: "Placeable Items"
	quest.0522CB444EDBF031.quest_desc: [
		"ike other &6Brass&r machines, the &6Brass Funnel&r can be set to &nFilter&r items. It can also be set to output or input either \"exactly\" or \"up to\" a set amount of items via its Value Settings Screen."
		""
		"When not on a Mechanical Belt, a &5Wrench&r can be used to set it to extract or insert. Otherwise, the direction of the belt determines whether the Funnel extracts or inserts."
		""
		"It can be turned off with Redstone."
	]
	quest.05CBA98839D0D1B9.quest_desc: ["A Coarse Mulch makes the Berry Tree act like it's in a Mountains or Taiga biome for an infinite duration."]
	quest.0611E32BAF6B62D2.quest_desc: ["A very high level hammer made of the metal of an ancient society pushed into the nether."]
	quest.0611E32BAF6B62D2.title: "Netherite Hammer: Tier VI"
	quest.063AE635AD0E0B31.quest_desc: ["The Adze is a shovel/axe combo that gives the advantages of both tools at a decreased speed due to its weight."]
	quest.06422AB7B816826E.quest_desc: ["When a Butt is added to a tool as a head it will increase the swing speed of the tool due to the decreased weight."]
	quest.06C807355C090380.quest_desc: [
		"Colonies have an area of claimed chunks (16x16 block areas) around them. Upon colony creation, a colony claims chunks in a square around it. "
		""
		"Those claims are protected from modification through other players."
		""
		"Extending your claim area can be done by building huts. Huts claim a square area around them after they are built, expanding all sides from the chunk the hutblock is located in. How much they claim depends on the building. They won’t claim over the max range"
		""
		"Deconstructing a building will remove the chunks it claimed."
	]
	quest.06C807355C090380.title: "===================Colony Border System==================="
	quest.06DF0442A4886D38.quest_desc: [
		"Two &6Crushing Wheels&r must be placed next to each other horizontally or vertically one block apart. Both wheels must be given opposite rotational force. Any items to be crushed must be inserted where the wheels rotate inwards."
		""
		"&6Crushing wheels&r can be automated by placing a vanilla hopper at the top directly between the wheels and either a depot or conveyor belt below. Materials will be fed through the top hopper."
		""
		"Some recipes have outputs that only happen by chance."
	]
	quest.06DF0442A4886D38.quest_subtitle: "Applies Crushing recipes to any items inserted from the direction they are spinning away from."
	quest.06FCFD49B9DC5C59.quest_desc: [
		""
		"- Any animals you slay using a Knife are guaranteed to drop secondary items, such as Leather and Feathers;"
		""
		"- Grassy plants (grass, wheat, rice etc) cut with a Knife will occasionally yield Straw, a firm and useful fiber;"
		""
		"- They act as a modest melee weapon: swings faster than a sword for lesser damage;"
		""
		"- Later on, they are also useful for cutting and portioning ingredients when preparing meals."
	]
	quest.06FCFD49B9DC5C59.quest_subtitle: "Knives are scavenging tools: they allow you to obtain a few more resources from both fauna and flora."
	quest.0706C5D73797D131.title: "Do it Coward"
	quest.07137122925727C8.quest_desc: ["Double Headed tools make up the large majority of tools in the game. The surrounding quests will describe the individual tool heads that define tools."]
	quest.07137122925727C8.quest_subtitle: "Place a vanilla tool such as a pickaxe, an axe or a hoe in a workbench and upgrade it"
	quest.073B8A584CDFD3AA.title: "Flamberge Blade"
	quest.07980ABDC8986709.quest_desc: [
		"The &6Andesite Funnel&r is used to extract or insert materials into inventories."
		""
		"While held, &6funnels&r prevent the player from accessing inventories, instead placing them. Sneak right clicking with a &6Funnel&r places it in input mode."
		""
		"Using a &5Wrench&r on the funnel switches it between input and output mode. Redstone can be applied to stop the funnel from inputting or outputting. Right-clicking a funnel on a Mechanical Belt causes it to extend one block forward."
		""
		"A &6Mechanical Belt&r is a mechanical component that conveys rotation and moves items and entities."
		""
		"To place down belts you will need 2 &7shafts&r facing in the same direction. They can be placed in 3 orientations, horizontal, vertical or diagonal at an 45° angle"
		""
		"Click on the first shaft and you will see some particle effects to where you are looking. When looking at a valid second shaft, these particles will turn green. Once you got a belt in place, it will relay rotation between the two shafts while keeping rotation and speed the same."
		""
		"You can also click a shaft onto any piece of a belt to insert an additional pulley that you can connect components to."
	]
	quest.07980ABDC8986709.title: "Belts"
	quest.07E84CCDE6208796.quest_desc: [
		"Here is the default method of converting Redstone Dust into Flux."
		""
		"Step 1: Find some Bedrock."
		""
		"Step 2: Place some Obsidian above it, leaving one block space in between"
		""
		"Step 3: Throw some Redstone Dust in the gap left by the Bedrock & Obsidian."
		""
		"Step 4: Left-click the Obsidian. The Obsidian will crush the Redstone Dust against the Bedrock and create Flux!"
		""
		"There is no limit to the amount of Redstone Dust you can use each time"
	]
	quest.07E84CCDE6208796.title: "Flux Networks"
	quest.08E2D490A361111F.quest_desc: ["The Chemical Injection Chamber uses &3Hydrogen Chloride gas&r to turn ores into 4 Shards. It is the start of x4 ore processing and requires a steady supply of Hydrogen Chloride, which in turn requires the player to have a &6Thermal Evaporation Plant&r running. "]
	quest.08E3DF822CEB83D2.title: "Rainbow Coal"
	quest.08FC281493BD7368.quest_desc: ["Can be made into a unique sword that cuts through stone."]
	quest.092202DA102742E4.quest_desc: [
		"- Repairing an item will require materials (and appropriate tools) for one of its modules"
		""
		"- Repairing will cycle over all of the item's modules"
		""
		"- Repairing magically unstable modules will cost experience"
		""
		"- Each repair fully restores the durability of the item"
	]
	quest.092202DA102742E4.quest_subtitle: "Modular items can be repaired in a workbench."
	quest.092202DA102742E4.title: "Repairing"
	quest.09D05DD705B6F75B.quest_desc: [
		"When this treatise is near a workbench any major module made of metal will do extra damage and have better efficiency."
		""
		"Can be bought from villagers who work metal."
	]
	quest.09F16718BC2A2AFD.quest_subtitle: "Find a scroll in the world or purchase it from villager"
	quest.0A9964481C4795E6.quest_desc: ["Ropes can be climbed like ladders. The ones from supplementaries can also be passed through."]
	quest.0A9964481C4795E6.title: "Ropes"
	quest.0ABE229CAA2C8D70.title: "Storage Drawers"
	quest.0AC80D084DE48B42.title: "Crucible Blade"
	quest.0AECCBA9318BEEA6.quest_subtitle: "Parkour"
	quest.0B03CA88F9FBC76B.title: "Wind Generator"
	quest.0BB92CBE08A783C6.quest_desc: ["A Humid Mulch makes the Berry Tree act like it's in a Jungle or Swamp biome for an infinite duration. "]
	quest.0BBD5E7CBD0E333B.title: "Lets Go Pikachu"
	quest.0C2503199855868B.title: "Smelting"
	quest.0C4AC3D8E92A6D73.quest_desc: [
		"This tier triples ingot yield for Silk-Touch'ed ores, or doubles the yield for standard raw ores. It starts by processing raw ores in the &zPurification Chamber&r. This machine is the first introduced in the ore processing pipeline that uses an additional input component as a part of processing its ore. In this case, the chamber uses Oxygen. From there, the processed items pass through the &9Crusher&r, then the &aEnrichment Chamber&r and are finally smelted into ingots."
		""
		""
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"    Raw Ore (Raw or Silk Touch'ed) + Oxygen → Purification Chamber → 2 or 3 Clumps"
		"    Clumps → Crusher → Dirty Dusts → Enrichment Chamber → Dusts → Energized Smelter → 2 or 3 Ingots"
	]
	quest.0C4AC3D8E92A6D73.quest_subtitle: "3x Ore Production"
	quest.0C881EDED56AD8E4.quest_subtitle: "Gather every seed from a Croptopia mod"
	quest.0C8C25608E7F0171.title: "Iron Age"
	quest.0D576E61BC0E0E26.quest_subtitle: "Train 30 soldiers"
	quest.0D58654CA3935CB7.quest_desc: [
		"/home [name] - Teleports to a home"
		""
		"/sethome <name> - Sets home"
		""
		"/delhome <name> - Deletes a home"
		""
		"/listhomes [player] - Lists all player homes"
	]
	quest.0D58654CA3935CB7.quest_subtitle: "You get more from Playtime!"
	quest.0D5F33E7E3155182.title: "Throw 100 Pokeballs"
	quest.0D69186F8138A0C9.quest_desc: [
		"When this treatise is near a workbench any major module made of gemstones will do extra damage and have better efficiency."
		""
		"Can be bought from mason villagers."
	]
	quest.0DC1979C19B9164F.title: "Hedge Maze"
	quest.0DD280C68907D4DE.quest_subtitle: "This world is inhabited by creatures called POKEMON!"
	quest.0E132FABA501393B.quest_subtitle: "Discover a Jungle Fortress"
	quest.0E4585C54A3E8C31.quest_desc: ["Place an animal's food in it and it will automatically breed animals for you"]
	quest.0F65ECE6E71A2171.quest_desc: [
		"The Dark Tower is found in a small clearing in the center of the dark forest. The center area has reddish, autumnal leaves and faded grass. The Dark Tower is the site of many eldritch experiments. The Ur-Ghast has taken over the top of the tower and must be vanquished to complete the Dark Forest phase of the adventure. "
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"Recommend bringing construction blocks as it will burn up the floor. "
	]
	quest.0F65ECE6E71A2171.quest_subtitle: "Dark Tower"
	quest.0F65ECE6E71A2171.title: "Ur-Ghast"
	quest.0FA22695304AE18C.quest_subtitle: "The Storage Unit"
	quest.0FA22BC0A8788511.quest_desc: ["This colorful tower sits roughly in the center of the Glacier. A variety of icy creatures dwell within the tower, while the Snow Queen awaits in a frost-covered room near the top. She is protected by a shield of ice and will attack with a barrage of icy attacks or charge into the adventurer."]
	quest.0FA22BC0A8788511.quest_subtitle: "Aurora Palace"
	quest.0FA22BC0A8788511.title: "Snow Queen"
	quest.0FEFCC67CC56A958.quest_desc: [
		"Throwing Knife: A schematic that allows you to make small swords that have the ability to be thrown."
		""
		"Howling Blade: A schematic of a sword fuller that when swung creates a gust that can deflect arrows."
		""
		"Sturdy Guard: A schematic that unlocks a long forgotten guard that allows you to block attacks or arrows with proper timing."
	]
	quest.0FEFCC67CC56A958.quest_subtitle: "Can be found in dungeons."
	quest.0FEFCC67CC56A958.title: "Schematics"
	quest.0FF4FFAF0C6CF495.quest_subtitle: "Visit a Beach"
	quest.0FF4FFAF0C6CF495.title: "Life is a Beach"
	quest.0FFBD03D30C69566.quest_desc: ["Rotation lock is enabled by pressing K by default on your keyboard. You will see a cube to the right of your crosshair. This makes all blocks you place face in the direction you were facing in when the lock was enabled. Press it again to change direction and again to turn it off."]
	quest.0FFBD03D30C69566.title: "Rotation Lock"
	quest.10756B8268EF9D31.quest_desc: ["Created by using a hoe on gravel."]
	quest.10836519F612623F.quest_desc: [
		"Rotten Apples have a chance to form if an apple item despawns on the ground. These green, wormy apples can be fed to a horse in order to turn it into a zombie horse. Note that you'll want to make sure the horse is tamed and saddled prior to this action. This zombification process will also preserve the speed and other aspects of the horse. Zombie horses cannot wear armor."
		""
		"Sinister Carrots are rarely found as loot in Woodland Mansions. They can be fed to a zombie horse in order to turn it into a skeleton horse. They can also be fed to a tamed rabbit to transform it into a Killer Rabbit, which can attack and is much stronger than a normal rabbit."
	]
	quest.10836519F612623F.title: "Rotten Apple and Sinister Carrot"
	quest.1108CE06BA6B894D.quest_subtitle: "ZA's worst Research"
	quest.11582E3001DAFF5F.quest_desc: ["Evolve a Gimmighoul after filling their Scrap Stash to 32/64/96/128/160/192/224/256"]
	quest.116D95959E34AE37.quest_desc: [
		"Fluids can be stored and extracted from fluid tanks via &9Fluid Pipe&r. The fluid pipes can be placed on any face of the fluid tank: top, bottom, or sides. The window of a tank can be toggled with a &6Wrench.&r"
		""
		"The direction of flow in the fluid pipe indicates whether fluids will be put into the tank or extracted from the tank; if fluid is flowing towards the tank, the fluid will be stored in the tank. Likewise, if a fluid pipe is flowing away from the tank (via &5Mechanical Pump&r), then fluid from the tank will be extracted into that pipe."
		""
		"Fluid tanks will merge with adjacent tanks, up to a maximum of 3x32x3, allowing to store up to 2,304 buckets of any fluid."
		""
		"The placement of fluid pipe connections to the tank is not important for functionality. For instance, an extracting pipe can be placed at the top of a tank and still remove fluid from the tank, even if the fluid tank is not completely full."
	]
	quest.116D95959E34AE37.quest_subtitle: "Can store up to 8 buckets"
	quest.11B9FE024020962D.quest_desc: [
		"The Chemical Washer turns Slurry into Clean Slurry using Water. The clean slurry then needs to be further refined by pumping it into a &9Chemical Crystallizer&r. "
		""
		"Note that unlike most Mekanism machines this one has fixed \"in\" and \"out\" sides for the mineral flow. \"In\" will be on the left when first placed and \"out\" is on the right. It can of course be rotated with the Configurator. Water is piped in through the top of the machine. "
	]
	quest.11D226CF2A5A318C.quest_subtitle: "Place a chtonic extractor on a bedrock and hit the top with a hammer"
	quest.1205D0D6C4DA06A3.quest_desc: ["As you explore the world, you’ll notice that there are some colonies abandoned by the former residents. Moving into one of these abandoned colonies is a way to quickstart your own colony!"]
	quest.1205D0D6C4DA06A3.title: "World Generation Colonies"
	quest.121E70CAE78BC36D.title: "Assembling your first Airship"
	quest.1223B74DE8108C67.quest_desc: [
		"The Cooking Table is the most important part of your kitchen. Right clicking on a Cooking Table will bring up a GUI which will tell you everything you can make with the food you have in your inventory and in inventories in your kitchen."
		""
		"Some food can be made instantly, while others have a cooking time. Some foods not only require ingredients, but also require certain kitchen appliances."
	]
	quest.1223B74DE8108C67.title: "Cooking Table"
	quest.12D605F59A3176A2.quest_subtitle: "Find ancient ruins deep down in cold or mountainous biomes"
	quest.12DAA083C8DAA20D.quest_desc: ["The Storage Pouch is a storage addon to store a good number of items but it does not have quick access."]
	quest.1320DB364BB5108B.title: "Level 5"
	quest.1355C48C0FAE2984.quest_desc: [
		"&6Smart Chutes&r behave similarly to Brass Funnels. They can be filtered to only allow certain items through, and be stopped with a redstone signal. Unlike funnels, they can insert and extract at the same time, but can only function vertically."
		""
		"When directly below an inventory, the Filter slot doubles as a Value Settings diode, much like the Brass Funnel. The Chute can be adjusted to extract up to or exactly a set amount of items. The Value Settings of a Smart Chute will be saved even when the inventory above is destroyed, though this has no effect on the Chute's behavior when not under an inventory."
	]
	quest.137A4FEB6C129118.quest_desc: [
		"The Sprinkler is a block which, when provided with a fluid using a pipe, will distribute it in a small area below."
		""
		"Different fluids can have different effects."
		""
		"- Lava applies a small amount of fire damage to entities below"
		""
		"- Water makes the area below wet, making the world think it's raining there."
		""
		"- Potions apply their affect for a short duration to entities below"
		""
		"- Liquid Fertilizer, a new fluid, applies a bonemeal affect to blocks."
	]
	quest.13BA37E45FCF1664.quest_desc: [
		"The &6Mechanical Arm&r can take or deposit items from various blocks within a 5 block radius of where it is placed. The order it does this in is determined by its behavior as well as the order the blocks were selected in during placement. A placed &6Mechanical Arm&r's selected blocks can be viewed by hovering over it with a Wrench."
		""
		"&lPlacement:&r"
		""
		"- With the Mechanical Arm in hand, right clicking valid inventories will select them."
		"- The arm will remember the order the blocks were selected in while transferring items."
		"- Right clicking again will toggle between taking items from the block (highlighted in blue) or depositing items to the block (highlighted in yellow.)"
		"- Left clicking will deselect the block."
		"- The Mechanical Arm can then be placed by right clicking on a block, and powered."
		"- Inventories beyond a 5 block radius from where it is placed will be dropped. The range of the arm can be adjusted in the Config."
		"- After placement, the amount of inputs and outputs an arm has will be shown in a message on screen if no selected points had to be dropped. A separate message is shown in red if interaction points were removed."
		"   -\"Mechanical Arm has x input(s) and y output(s)\""
		"   -\"x selected interaction point(s) removed due to range limitations\""
		""
		"After the arm is placed, the inventories will be saved relative to where the arm is rather than by their coordinates; when the arm is moved, it will check for inventories relative to its current location, dropping them if no valid inventory is found."
		""
		"The arm can be powered by a Cogwheel or similar blocks."
	]
	quest.13E34F201E1FB2CD.quest_subtitle: "Holder for DataModels"
	quest.145F74705341F30E.quest_subtitle: "Find all new outposts(14)"
	quest.1478BE654172DB0E.quest_desc: ["The Potion Bag allows you to cary a large amount of potions but of limited variety."]
	quest.147EABFC7C5BB8FF.quest_desc: ["A Peat Mulch makes the Berry Tree act like it's in a Forest biome for an infinite duration. "]
	quest.1492F3C3FB608067.quest_desc: ["The Booster is a sort of jetpack that uses gunpowder as fuel. Can be activated by crouch jumping, jumping in air, or while flying an elytra."]
	quest.14CB95291255A8BE.title: "Halberd"
	quest.15069CA263BFE7ED.title: "Rending scissors Blade"
	quest.15358C492A96474A.quest_desc: [
		"When this treatise is near a workbench any major module made of fibre will do extra damage and have better efficiency."
		""
		"Can be bought from fletcher villagers."
	]
	quest.154A69FDD3CF3D18.quest_desc: [
		"Free Runners are an item that allows players to ascend 1-block inclines automatically (like the Horse), as well as preventing fall damage as long as they are charged. "
		""
		"A fall will reduce the item's charge, depending on how far the fall was. "
	]
	quest.1551E4FD839807A2.quest_desc: ["The Oven is a block which can be used to cook food very quickly. Right click on the Oven to open its GUI. Place food you want to cook into the top 3 slots of the oven. It will automatically be moved into the 9 central slots as it cooks. Cooked food will then be moved to the 3 slots on the right. You can shift right click the front of the Oven to open the door and put food into it without opening the GUI. Shift right click again to close the door. Connecting an Oven to your kitchen unlocks recipes which require smelting. The oven requires fuel to run. Place fuel (coal for example) in the left-most slot to heat up the Oven. "]
	quest.1551E4FD839807A2.title: "Cooking for Blockheads"
	quest.156ECC53DB98ED6A.title: "Cane"
	quest.159670F55DD10CD9.quest_desc: ["Acts as a Storage Controller when linked to it"]
	quest.15AEB8885DE3D188.quest_desc: [
		"The first step in making better gear will be by upgrading your hammer to Stone (Tier II)."
		""
		"To upgrade a hammer you will need another hammer to do so, hence the reward from the previous quest."
	]
	quest.15BC51D7F5324998.quest_subtitle: "Get a full suit of Netherite armor"
	quest.165C637A0F04D7FD.quest_desc: ["Places random blocks from your hotbar. Useful for making natural looking walls and paths."]
	quest.1675016F56430825.quest_desc: ["The energized smelter is your basic electric furnace that uses energy instead of fuel to smelt items. "]
	quest.16C6FF16D8C651A1.title: "Magic 8ball"
	quest.1729A82B2351DE53.quest_desc: [
		"When any growable plant is placed on Rich Soil, its growth will be randomly boosted, similar to the usage of Bone Meal."
		"Rich Soil can be tilled into Rich Farmland through the use of hoes. Rich Farmland is immune to mob trampling and won't unravel to Melons or Pumpkins, but requires hydration in order to boost crops."
		""
		"Mushrooms planted on Rich Soil under sufficient darkness will eventually form a Mushroom Colony. Such colonies will grow from 2 to 5 mushroom caps over time, dropping them when harvested."
	]
	quest.1783F3551BE3CC14.quest_desc: [
		"The Wooden Hammer will be your first tool on your smithing journey."
		""
		"Check the advancements tabs to gather greater info on the mod outside of these quests."
		""
	]
	quest.1783F3551BE3CC14.title: "Wooden Hammer: Tier I"
	quest.17A7564E50233D43.quest_desc: ["A strait bow is a standard bow giving average draw time and damage."]
	quest.18C9EDD4E37799EC.quest_desc: [
		"The &6Windmill Bearing&r is a block used for power generation."
		""
		"A &5windmill&r is created by attaching any block to the front of the &6Windmill Bearing&r to act as a hub, then attaching multiple &nsail&r blocks to the hub bock. The &6Windmill Bearing&r comes with glue already on the face to which the hub block attaches. Additional blocks may be attached with &2Super Glue&r. The additional blocks are decorative only. Only the sail blocks generate power."
		""
		"&nSail blocks&r include &5Windmill Sails&r, &5Sail Frames&r, and Wool blocks. A minimum of &neight&r sails are required. Sails will automatically connect to each other and to blocks that have already been attached. The sails can be placed in any configuration; the shape does not matter."
		""
		"Right-click the &6Windmill Bearing&r anywhere but the center with an empty hand to start the windmill. To stop it, right-click on the block with an empty hand again. To change the spin direction, right-click and hold on the center of the bearing where a circular arrow appears. Hold down the right mouse key and either scroll the wheel or move the mouse left and right to select the direction."
	]
	quest.18C9EDD4E37799EC.title: "Windmill"
	quest.18F8DADD01FEC9C2.quest_desc: [
		"The Cooking Pot is a workstation where you can both prepare and store a large amount of meals. When placed above any suitable heat source (campfire, open flames, lava, a stove etc.), it will start bubbling, indicating it's ready to cook."
		""
		"You can put up to six ingredients inside a pot. If they match, the pot will start cooking them up into a meal. Most meals need a container to be served on, such as Bowls; the result slot will tell you which one to use. Simply add the container on the corresponding slot, or right-click the pot with it, to take a serving!"
		""
		"Meals tend to be quite large, so they don't stack up as high in your inventory. If you're not going to eat them all right away, you can just mine the whole pot and take it with you! Cooking Pots can hold 64 servings of any meal with a container, regardless of their maximum stack limit."
	]
	quest.18FB6AA280646F14.quest_subtitle: "Delve deep underground"
	quest.19012C596BCE8C3E.quest_desc: ["Integrity is an item statistic that determines if it can be upgraded or not. Certain upgrades, such as bindings and handles, will increase the integrity of a tool allowing it to be upgraded further."]
	quest.19012C596BCE8C3E.title: "Integrity Through Bindings?"
	quest.1922E3B2FEE67377.quest_subtitle: "Find a Gym Bro"
	quest.197AE51E423835D4.quest_desc: [
		"Gantry Carriages are a Contraption that will collide with unmovable blocks in their path."
		""
		"Place Gantry Shafts along where the Gantry Carriage will move. Apply Rotational power to the shafts to move the Carriage along them, and invert the power to move it back. Inverting the placement of the shafts will invert all movement. Use a Wrench to help change the orientation."
		""
		"Apply a Redstone signal to the shaft to stop the carriage and send rotational power through the Carriage's output. This can be used to move another attached Gantry Carriage."
		""
		"Gantry Shafts attached to the Carriage's output will move along with them automatically."
		""
		"Multiple Carriages on one shaft can also move the same structure built onto it."
	]
	quest.19A4385584636C45.quest_desc: [
		"The Stove is a direct upgrade to the Campfire's cooking features, and a suitable heat source for the Cooking Pot."
		""
		"To add items to its grill, simply right-click the Stove when it has no objects blocking its top face. Stoves detect campfire recipes to cook, meaning they usually also take 30 seconds to fully prepare items. Stoves cannot be automated through item transferring blocks (e.g. Hoppers), but require no fuel to cook items, much like a Campfire."
		""
		"Stoves can hold six (6) items on its grill, and will gently pop cooked outputs above its surface, instead of throwing them around."
		""
		"Stoves can be put out using shovels or buckets of water, and reignited with Flint and Steel."
	]
	quest.19A4385584636C45.title: "Farmer's Delight"
	quest.1A01E6EA78F32D04.quest_desc: ["These strong doors can be locked with a key and can be opened with your hand."]
	quest.1A1032A815E0BEE0.quest_desc: ["Put a hopper above it and it will drop all items below it."]
	quest.1A565B02E67D7872.title: "Tool Storage"
	quest.1AADDD5AD372A4D4.quest_desc: ["The mod includes various wands (Reset, Linking, League) to help interface with the various systems"]
	quest.1AC0EE6A2DC56D21.title: "Find Portal Ruins"
	quest.1AD3B839B690E37D.quest_desc: [
		"&9&nHolding Items&r&r"
		""
		"Items can be &4right clicked&r or inserted onto the depot. Machines such as Mechanical Presses will interact with the items the same way they would on a Mechanical Belt."
		""
		"Items on a depot &3will not despawn&r, and will stay there until they are extracted by a player or another machine."
		""
		"&9&nDisplay Link&r&r"
		""
		"Depots can be sources for &6Display Links&r. As well as displaying the name of the item in the depot, items held by other depots placed in a row behind the main depot will be displayed."
	]
	quest.1ADB6E725663B3AB.quest_desc: ["The Claw head will allow you to pry open items in Tetra dungeons as well as break wooden items quickly."]
	quest.1B166861840A1636.quest_desc: ["Throwable Explosive that only breaks grass, torches and other weak blocks. Aim at a mob's feet to send them flying!"]
	quest.1BD22FC74CD3DB9A.quest_desc: [
		"The Holosphere is given to the player with the first hammer that is created (though it also can be crafted again later if lost). The left menu (CRFT) is currently the only one available."
		""
		"In the holosphere you will be able to check all the materials and their statistics as components. It is very useful in planning out your next tool upgrade."
	]
	quest.1BD22FC74CD3DB9A.title: "Holosphere"
	quest.1C3B786EEFD794D8.quest_desc: ["Nothing in this modpack or community server is paid. This is just a friendly sort of challenge series. Previous Seasons will never be inaccessible. "]
	quest.1C3B786EEFD794D8.title: "Season One: Fiery Grave"
	quest.1D000AA51F0BDD77.quest_desc: [
		"When Rotational Force is given to the &6Hose Pully&r, it can extend the hose infinitely. Reversing the Rotational Force will retract the hose back to the block. The hose of the &6Hose Pully&r must be extended by at least one block before it can function."
		""
		"A &9Fluid Pump&r is required for the hose to drain or flood liquids."
		""
		"- If a fluid is &cpumped out&r, it will drain a body of liquid down to the level of the hose. If multiple hose pulleys draw from the same source, it will effectively expedite the drainage process, provided that the pipe's capacity is maintained."
		""
		"- If a fluid is &2pumped in&r, it will flood a room of any size, with the hose marking the highest point of flooding."
		""
		"- If a liquid source is at least 10,000 blocks the &6Hose Pulley&r considers it to be infinite, drawing the liquid from it without actually draining the source. Reintroducing the same liquid into the infinite source will deplete the fluid. This is also the maximum flood volume in blocks."
	]
	quest.1D000AA51F0BDD77.quest_subtitle: "Lets down a hose that can drain bodies of liquids."
	quest.1D2603396BCBAE65.quest_desc: [
		""
		"“A dragon without its rider is a tragedy."
		"A rider without their dragon is dead.” "
	]
	quest.1D2603396BCBAE65.title: "Dragon Slayer"
	quest.1D29CFDF2B56107B.quest_subtitle: "Gather every sapling from a Croptopia mod"
	quest.1D3EDFD37AFCCB25.quest_desc: [
		"Geodes are gained as a random chance from mining Deepslate."
		""
		"To break open these geodes place them in a workbench where they can be opened with a hammer."
		"From them you can gain random resources and even rare prisitine versions of gems."
	]
	quest.1D71BA7DA68CF606.quest_desc: ["This is just your standard sword blade with no extra frills."]
	quest.1D71C57E9B52C64D.quest_desc: [
		"One of the more basic generators is called the &6Water Wheel&r. This concept should sound familiar, especially to people that have been playing modded minecraft for a bit. To get it spinning, all you have to do is get some water flowing around it. "
		""
		"Pay attention the direction the water is flowing though, as it will spin at only half the rate when water flows in the wrong direction."
	]
	quest.1D71C57E9B52C64D.quest_subtitle: "Hover over this block in your inventory and hold 'W' to see how it works and how to assemble it correctly"
	quest.1D90D810E787E7E0.quest_desc: ["Can be hammered into bedrock to gain resources or added to a pickaxe to make a unique mining tool to break multiple blocks at a time."]
	quest.1DAAC3F3FF329157.quest_desc: ["To use &eSand Paper&r, hold it in the offhand, and &dRose Quartz&r in the main hand. The quartz will get polished, and drop on the ground. One durability will be used off the paper."]
	quest.1DAAC3F3FF329157.title: "Electron Tube"
	quest.1E87BCA90B5A45AA.quest_desc: ["Time to head to the nether to get some fine heat treated Blackstone that is surprisingly stronger than basic metals."]
	quest.1EA89DD440FBA503.quest_subtitle: "Breed all the animals!(26)"
	quest.1F06255C02B6AED5.quest_desc: [
		"When crafting tool upgrades they will require tools of various specialities to be worked into their final forms."
		""
		"Wood materials will require axes, metals and stones will require hammers, and organic materials will require cutting tools such as swords to be able to be crafted."
		"For progressively higher levels of materials the required tool level will equally be as high, this drives you to equally maintain your tool levels in order to keep progress moving."
		""
		"So keep upgrading those hammers to keep getting the best gear!"
	]
	quest.1F1DE1A663B7BED4.quest_desc: ["The fearsome Hydra is found in a converted Hollow Hill in the middle of the Fire Swamp. There is no maze or dungeon to navigate, as the hydra does not need any protection from intruders. Good luck! If you survive, make contact with the Hydra's Fiery Blood and the Swamp phase of the adventure will be complete. "]
	quest.1F1DE1A663B7BED4.quest_subtitle: "Fire Swamp"
	quest.1F1DE1A663B7BED4.title: "Hydra"
	quest.1F6F9D8EB4E53575.quest_desc: ["The longbow has increased drawtime in comparison to a standard bow but it has much more strength and will do increased damage."]
	quest.1F6F9D8EB4E53575.title: "Longbow"
	quest.1F748A5323AB86E5.quest_subtitle: "First Step in Resource Production"
	quest.1F748A5323AB86E5.title: "CobbleWorkers"
	quest.1FBD746595917646.quest_desc: [
		"When this treatise is near a workbench any major module made of fabric will do extra damage and have better efficiency."
		""
		"Can be bought from shepard villagers."
	]
	quest.1FDC3C084B826D88.quest_desc: [
		"The &6Item Drain&r can hold up to 1500mb of fluid at a time. A &9Fluid Pump&r is needed to extract the fluid."
		""
		"A &5Basin&r will automatically deposit output fluids into an &6Item Drain&r placed near it."
	]
	quest.1FDC3C084B826D88.quest_subtitle: "Drains fluid from items such as buckets and bottles inserted onto it"
	quest.2031C7013AC15F55.quest_desc: ["Can be placed on top of sticks to create a flagpole. Right-click a flagpole to raise the flag, hold sneak to lower it."]
	quest.2031C7013AC15F55.title: "Flags"
	quest.206FE38B596D60E7.quest_desc: [
		"The Drawer Key will allow you to lock an item to a storage drawer slot. This will lock that item into that slot, even when all items are removed from the drawer."
		""
		"The Quantify Key will allow you to show/hide the storage drawer display of the number of items contained on the face of the drawer."
	]
	quest.20D47F19D03BD8C2.quest_desc: [
		"&9&nInteracting&r&r"
		""
		"The &6Deployer&r can be given items to use with machines or by right clicking the items into the hand."
		""
		"The &6Deployer&r can be stopped with a &4Redstone&r signal."
		""
		"&5The Filter&r on the side of the &6Deployer&r can be adjusted to only use certain items. The filter is also essential when using a Deployer in a Contraption."
		""
		"The Deployer has 2 inventory slots; the held item and one extra internal slot. As well as unusable items, items harvested by the &6Deployer&r will be transferred to the extra slot to be removed by machines, during which time the Deployer will stall. Items cannot be extracted from the extra slot directly by the player."
		""
		"The &6Deployer&r simulates right clicks by default. It can be adjusted to left click instead by right clicking the front with a Wrench. While in left-click mode, the &6Deployer&r can use normal tools, such as pickaxes and swords. The tools will behave as if the player was holding them, including mobs dropping rare items when slain by a &6Deployer.&r"
		""
		"&9&nSchematic Printing&r&r"
		""
		"When given a Schematic for a filter, a deployer on a Contraption can print structures if supplied with materials. Keep in mind the position of the Schematic must be set beforehand. The deployer must be moved in range of the Schematic's position in order to place blocks. The deployer will only place blocks if there are none in the way."
		""
		"Unlike the Schematicannon, the Schematic is not consumed, allowing for a structure to be printed multiple times."
		""
		"&9&nSequenced Assembly&r&r"
		""
		"When positioned &nabove&r a &1Mechanical Belt&r or &9Depot,&r the &6Deployer&r can use held items to build components like the Cogwheel and Precision Mechanism. Each component built in this manner can require multiple passes and has a percentage chance of producing random junk rather than the intended item."
	]
	quest.20D47F19D03BD8C2.quest_subtitle: "Simulates player actions on blocks or entities exactly 2 blocks away from it."
	quest.2140BB56455664BA.quest_subtitle: "Use a Planar Stabilizer to craft a powerful belt attachment"
	quest.216F8320B52B65C1.quest_desc: [
		"When this treatise is near a workbench any major module made of wood will do extra damage and have better efficiency."
		""
		"Can be bought from fletcher villagers."
	]
	quest.216FB2664241E7F3.title: "Alolan Roll"
	quest.2180E83A0BF99108.quest_subtitle: "Build, light and enter the nether portal"
	quest.21CEC05CBFEA8B0E.quest_subtitle: "Explore all Nether biomes"
	quest.21DA1CC37A474873.quest_desc: [
		"The &6Mechanical Mixer&r is powered by an internal cogwheel, and will behave as one to any adjacent components, relaying and reversing rotation sideways."
		""
		"&6The Mixer&r requires a minimum rotational speed of &n30 RPM&r from its power source to work. Mixers will process ingredients faster the more speed it is given."
		""
		"To work, a &6Mixer&r must be placed directly above a &1Basin,&r with a 1 block gap. When a valid recipe is inserted by throwing the ingredients in the &6Mixer,&r the Mixer will automatically combine the ingredients."
		""
		"All &nshapeless crafting recipes&r can be made automatically using the &6Mechanical Mixer&r by inserting required items into the &1Basin&r under the mixer."
		""
		"All &nBrewing recipes&r can be made automatically using the &6Mechanical Mixer&r by inserting the required items and fluids into the &1Basin&r under the mixer. Brewing recipes require heating with a &eblaze burner&r."
	]
	quest.21E603791EEC455B.quest_desc: [
		"The TEP is built on a 4x4 base of Thermal Evaporation Blocks and has a height of at least 3 blocks. All layers above the base are hollow. To increase the internal storage and rate of evaporation, the structure can be raised up to 18 blocks high. A Thermal Evaporation Controller is required and is used to open the user interface. Thermal Evaporation Valves are used for input/output of fluids and for supplying heat via Resistive Heaters. The top layer doesn't require blocks in the corners."
		""
		"Important: Allowed placement of Thermal Evaporation Controllers and Thermal Evaporation Valves is anywhere in an inside wall(not a corner) OR on the corners of the top layer only, which can be useful if you lower the TEP into the ground."
		" "
		"Requires 1 Resistive Heater or up to 4 Advanced Solar Generators added to the top layer in order to provide heat for the TEP. "
	]
	quest.21E603791EEC455B.quest_subtitle: "MutliBlock Structure"
	quest.22E1A465FAF7EAA2.quest_desc: ["Fully absorbs your fall without dealing damage."]
	quest.2301392C37F63AAC.quest_subtitle: "Have an army of 80"
	quest.239CA302D0E9B38F.quest_desc: [
		"Right click the front of a &6Mechanical Crafter&r with a &5Wrench&r to change the direction it sends items during crafting. The &6Mechanical Crafters&r are only connected by this path."
		""
		"Mechanical Crafters can be automatically filled by &9Funnels&r or &7Hoppers.&r"
		""
		"On the back and sides of Mechanical Crafters, a Wrench can be used to connect or disconnect the inventory of two adjacent crafters. Crafters can share inventories while not participating in the same crafting recipe."
		""
		"&oItems can also be inserted or removed by hand.&r"
		""
		"Each &6Mechanical Crafter&r has an internal gear that can only be powered by adjacent Mechanical Crafters or any size Cogwheel. This means only 1 &6Mechanical Crafter&r in a setup needs to be powered by a &5Cogwheel.&r"
		""
		"Once a recipe is assembled in the final &6Crafter,&r the item will either be placed into the inventory of the block the Crafter's path sends items to, or will be ejected into the world at that side of the Crafter if no such block exists."
		""
		"If the final Crafter directs the finished product back into the recipe, the item must be manually removed from the Crafters by a player."
	]
	quest.23B0977C84937676.title: "Craft all Basic Pokeballs"
	quest.2437C58209463C36.quest_desc: [" It pulls items from an adjacent inventory"]
	quest.245946FF40FEFEE2.quest_desc: ["The Axe head allows you to chop tree logs and strip them just like vanilla axes."]
	quest.248343A8203E7CDC.quest_desc: ["Single Headed tools are the most simple tools you can make."]
	quest.2498696001EEAE22.title: "Twilight Forest"
	quest.24EA65D8B4F870AC.title: "Catch Dreepy"
	quest.24F3E4A8F52EF884.quest_desc: ["Of course, having gone through all that, there is a big, white, majestic castle atop the plateau: The Final Castle. There is almost nothing in it, but perhaps one day in the future, there will be. "]
	quest.24F3E4A8F52EF884.quest_subtitle: "WIP since 2011"
	quest.24F3E4A8F52EF884.title: "Final Castle"
	quest.258295FE630451F9.title: "Hit Level 30"
	quest.25ACF5942E55453B.quest_desc: ["Robit is Mekanism's mechanical companion. It can act as a crafting grid, a furnace, an anvil, a chest, or simply a cute little buddy. It is immune to fire, including the Flamethrower. "]
	quest.25C3FEF10032939D.quest_desc: [
		"The Teleporter Portal is a multi-block structure that allows the player to teleport between Teleporters on the same frequency. They are configured by right-clicking the Teleporter block at the base of the Teleporter."
		""
		"Their security can be configured as \"Public\" (any player can teleport between Teleporters on this frequency) or \"Private\" (only the player who created/belonging to that frequency may use or add Teleporter Portals to it). They can be used to travel between dimensions. "
	]
	quest.25C3FEF10032939D.title: "Teleporter"
	quest.2625EC5BE51DE54D.quest_desc: [
		"Thermal Cells can be found in Ancient Bases as loot."
		""
		"They can be charged in Transfer Units attached to operating Core Extractor units. The side of the Transfer Unit must be pried off to be able to plug cells in."
	]
	quest.2625EC5BE51DE54D.title: "Thermal Cells and Recharging"
	quest.262F18757D051B57.quest_subtitle: "You're the real diamond"
	quest.266C0AB38112B333.quest_desc: [
		"Animal Tamers can be found in villages in their own unique houses or can be created with a unemployed villager using a pet bed as a workstation. They trade a variety of items related to animals from both vanilla minecraft and this mod, including unique pet enchants(charisma)."
		""
		"Their houses also contain some untamed mobs and sometimes fish tanks."
	]
	quest.266C0AB38112B333.title: "Animal Tamer Villager"
	quest.26A723555347A7EC.title: "Visit Nether Wasteland"
	quest.26BD01F8DDF3A77E.quest_desc: ["Allow exiting players to trigger gym resets so that everything is put back in place for the next player!"]
	quest.26C39E92EBC7473A.quest_desc: ["Turns raw ores into slurry using Sulfuric Acid. The machine uses 100 mB of sulfuric acid for every ore dissolved and outputs 1000 mb of slurry. This slurry needs washing in the &bChemical Washer&r. It is also used in the production of Fissile Fuel. "]
	quest.26ECFBA1C3F2FD65.quest_subtitle: "It was made in 2014"
	quest.26ECFBA1C3F2FD65.title: "I've got a Record Player"
	quest.272AB75D83E37084.quest_subtitle: "The Elgance"
	quest.275F5DB06665BEFF.quest_subtitle: "The Binding"
	quest.27878287C6D742FA.title: "Explorer's Compass"
	quest.278F7867670C71D3.title: "Lunar Roll"
	quest.27A4548599B02459.quest_desc: ["The Cart Assembler can be placed on Rails. When the assembler is powered with redstone, blocks placed on top of the assembler will be attached to minecarts that pass through it as a Contraption. Use Block Attachment Utilities to attach more blocks."]
	quest.27E4CBB51DBD27CD.quest_desc: [
		"Ropes are essentially reverse scaffolding: the can be continuously deployed downward from the same spot, and can be climbed without collision. This allows players to safely descend or ascend high altitudes, such as ravines or mountains."
		""
		"When placing Rope, you can use more ropes against the first one to deploy them downward. This will continuously extend a column of rope down to the bottom-most Y-level possible, allowing for easy and controllable descents into chasms, ravines or from high locations."
		""
		"To suppress rope deployment, simply sneak while placing it. If there's no space underneath to deploy, it will also place normally."
	]
	quest.2820B936810CE69D.title: "Infuse The Fragment"
	quest.286C78DD09FE49B1.quest_desc: [
		"The Workbench will be where all the magic will happen with Tetra."
		""
		"This block is created by right clicking a Crafting Table with the Wooden Hammer you just created."
		""
		"By right clicking the workbench it will open a menu where an item (which types can be seen below in the branching quests) can then be placed and modified."
	]
	quest.290A2645FBD90100.quest_subtitle: "Enter an overworld city"
	quest.2A2564C1243BCD7B.quest_subtitle: "An Origin Ball"
	quest.2A2564C1243BCD7B.title: "Login 3 Weeks"
	quest.2B0716D508D81885.quest_subtitle: "We all start somewhere"
	quest.2B0716D508D81885.title: "Beginner Trainer"
	quest.2B4D2CECE651C777.quest_desc: [
		"&n&6Mechanical Bearing&r&r"
		""
		"When the &6Mechanical Bearing&r is powered with Rotational Force, right clicking the bearing will start the rotation so long as there is a potential structure connected to the front of it."
		""
		"The structure will rotate. If another &6Mechanical Bearing&r is used within a Contraption, facing the same way as the original, the blocks attached to that bearing will keep their alignment as the rest of the structure moves."
		""
		"A bearing contraption does not collide with blocks unless the appropriate Contraption Actor makes the collision."
		""
		"&oShift-right-clicking on a Mechanical Bearing with a Wrench will destroy the Mechanical Bearing and place it in your inventory.&r"
		""
		"&n&6Linear Chassis&r&r"
		""
		"&6Linear Chassis&r will automatically connect to adjacent and equally aligned chassis. &2Slime Balls&r or &aSuper Glue&r are needed to connect a column of other blocks to either of their piston-like surfaces. The Slime or Super Glue is not consumed on use. A &5Wrench&r can be used to adjust the size of the column by hovering over the side and scrolling. Hold ctrl with a Wrench to adjust all connected Chassis at once. A Clipboard can also be used to view, copy, and paste the chassis' settings."
		""
		"Secondary Linear Chassis can be used to have adjacent chassis that don't connect to each other."
		""
		"Chassis are directional; if something moves the blocks in the chassis' column but not the chassis itself, it won't move the chassis."
		""
		"&n&6Radial Chassis&r&r"
		""
		"Unlike &5Linear Chassis&r, the &6Radial Chassis&r connects to a radius of blocks around it rather than a straight line of blocks. This can be unwieldy if there are blocks nearby one would rather not connect to the Contraption."
		""
		"You can right click on the sides of the chassis while holding a &2Slimeball&r or &aSuper Glue&r to make them sticky, and again to apply it to all sides. The items are not consumed. The radius of affected blocks can be changed per chassis with a Wrench. Hold Ctrl to scroll every connected chassis."
		""
		"&a&nSuper Glue&r&r"
		""
		"Super glue has two modes of application: Block by Block Mode and Area Mode. These modes can be intermixed on the same contraption."
		""
		"In &3block-by-block&r mode, super glue is used just like a Slimeball. Right clicking on a Linear Chassis or Radial Chassis while holding the super glue, coats the face of a chassis with green glue allowing other blocks to be attached."
		""
		"&3Area mode&r is used to glue collections of blocks together after they have been placed. Glue a 3-D section of blocks by right clicking a block on one corner of the section while holding the super glue. Move the cursor to the opposite corner of the section. A green box will appear indicating the blocks which will be glued together. Right click again to complete the glueing process. To abort the process, right click while sneaking."
	]
	quest.2B56976F11F9263F.quest_desc: [
		"- Before the Raid"
		"As your colony develops, you may get raided by hostile forces. These forces can spawn almost anywhere except near your buildings. Generally, this means they’ll spawn outside of the colony, but if your buildings are spread out, they could spawn between them!"
		""
		"Raids will only spawn at the start of a night. There will be a chat message giving a general direction of where the raid spawned and a bar at the top of your screen showing your progress in defeating the raiders. Raids spawn randomly, with a minimum number of nights between them and an average number of nights as set in the config file. Larger colonies may get multiple waves or groups of raiders from different directions, even of different types. Be careful!"
		""
		"If you have a Barracks at level 3 or higher, you can hire spies to make raiders glow. This can help you find that one pesky raider that got stuck or is hiding and finish the raid."
		""
		"- During the Raid"
		"Raiders will run around the colony breaking down doors and trying to attack your Guards and colonists. Generally, raiders will path toward hut blocks in your colony, similar to what Guards do on patrol.Trying to “cheese” the raiders usually will not work. They are able to path fairly well, though if they are unable to find any path to their destination, they will break through any block, place ladders to climb up obstacles, or place blocks to bridge gaps to get to your colony. They can swim straight through moving water and lava, taking no damage from lava. Any attack that hits a raider too hard will be reflected back at the attacker. Similarly, turrets (from other mods) generally will not be effective on raiders.Raiders have a chance to drop their equipment when you or your Guards defeat them. They may also drop Ancient Tomes, which are used in enchanting."
		""
		"- After the Raid"
		"After all of the raiders have been defeated and spawners broken, your colonists will go back to their jobs. If any of your colonists die, then their family will mourn their death and not work that day. However, Guards will not be mourned."
	]
	quest.2B56976F11F9263F.quest_subtitle: "If a raid is currently in progress, your colonists will stop working and run home!"
	quest.2BF56D0E5F47DFFE.title: "Z-Ring"
	quest.2BFFB238D31D61AB.quest_desc: ["The Hoe head will allow you to harvest crops and till soil to farm just like a standard hoe."]
	quest.2C1C0E127A96B892.quest_desc: [
		"While cogwheels can be used as fancy looking shafts, their main use is a little different. "
		""
		"They will &nrelay rotation sideways&r to other cogwheels while keeping the axis of rotation. Directly adjacent cogwheels will also reverse the direction of rotation."
		""
		"When mixing &4large&r and &2small&r cogwheel the speed of rotation will also change"
		""
		"&nTwo&r large cogwheels at an 90° Angle allow for the axis of rotation to be changed."
	]
	quest.2C1FA53EDCCA95B8.quest_desc: ["The Deed of Ownership is an item that can be purchased from the Animal Tamer villager. By right clicking on a tamed pet that you are the owner of, you bind it to the deed. If you give the deed to any other player, and they use it on the bounded animal, then the ownership of the pet will pass onto them, making it effectively as if they were the ones who tamed the animal."]
	quest.2CC54414157DB5D9.quest_desc: ["30 minutes of Flight. Expires on death, dimension transfer, or logout."]
	quest.2CC54414157DB5D9.title: "Flight Coupon"
	quest.2D00608E23BFE28D.quest_subtitle: "Enchant a stonecutter with the efficient enchantment to increase the amount of blocks broken in each sweep"
	quest.2DA3FB6EF0E426B2.quest_subtitle: "Energy Transfer"
	quest.2DADDB2315AB67D6.quest_desc: [
		"There are dozens of new dungeons, some of them are guarded with Bosses."
		"What are you waiting for? Go conquer them all!"
	]
	quest.2DADDB2315AB67D6.quest_subtitle: "New dungeons and challenges"
	quest.2DAF14EBB2686543.title: "Time and Space Travel"
	quest.2DB16E3FA1CA6062.quest_desc: ["A Rich Mulch increases the yield of the harvest of the Berry Tree that it is used on for 3 harvests. "]
	quest.2E04F5C0A35B5262.quest_desc: [
		"This tier doubles ingot yield by pre-processing the raw ores in an Enrichment Chamber before smelting into ingots."
		""
		"1 Silk Touch Ore → Enrichment Chamber → 2 Dusts → Energized Smelter → 2 Ingots "
	]
	quest.2E04F5C0A35B5262.quest_subtitle: "2x Ore Processing"
	quest.2E6E875A43A3D7F1.quest_desc: [
		"Fishing with a Poké Rod whilst using a Love Ball bobber. Has the same other conditions as a regular Wooper."
		""
		""
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"Based on the appearance of a Wooper owned by Olesia, which appeared in the anime episode \"No Big Woop!\". They are nigh-identical to a regular Wooper, aside from a heart-shaped mark on their chest in place of the top curved mark. Their shiny is the same as a regular Wooper. "
	]
	quest.2EB653CBB74BFDF4.quest_desc: [
		"&6Blaze Burners&r are used for Heating and Super-Heating Basins when doing Mixing recipes. In particular, they are required to make &eBrass.&r They can also be used as a heat source for boilers used to power Steam Engines. When a heat-able block is placed above a fueled Blaze Burner, the Burner will appear to channel heat into the block."
		""
		"&nRight-clicking&r a Blaze Burner with &nany&r item that can be used as Furnace fuel will temporarily put it in a Heated state. "
		"&nRight-clicking&r a Blaze Burner with a &nBlaze Cake&r will temporarily put it in a Super-Heated state."
		""
		"Fuel burn time is the same as a vanilla Furnace. The Blaze inside changes its size and texture depending on the amount of fuel provided, following the phases:"
		""
		"&lPhase 1&r — Smouldering — Does not provide any heat for mixing, but provides the \"passive\" heat level for boilers. This is the default state when placing the Burner or when the fuel runs out."
		""
		"&lPhase 2&r — Heated/Kindled — Enables recipes that require heating. Lasts for the fuel's burn time and provides 1 heating level to Steam Engines per Blaze Burner"
		""
		"&lPhase 3&r — Super-Heated/Seething — Enables every Mixing recipe and provides 2 heating levels to Steam Engines per Blaze Burner. Only achievable using the Blaze Cake. Always lasts for 160 seconds. The Blaze Burner cannot be re-fed during this phase."
		""
		"A &5Deployer&r or &5Mechanical Arm&r can be used to automatically fuel it, given any burnable item as an input. Lava Buckets can be put into the Blaze Burner, and the Bucket will not be consumed."
	]
	quest.2EB653CBB74BFDF4.quest_subtitle: "Can be used for heating Steam Engines, Bulk Smoking, Bulk Smelting"
	quest.2EC20B2A4F142192.title: "Kill the Warden"
	quest.2FAB5C1CB4B02BF5.quest_subtitle: "Mekanism Part 2"
	quest.2FC282739157D6DB.quest_desc: ["You can set it to speak a message or show it in chat. Perfect for annoying your friends (or enemies!)"]
	quest.2FEC85DD348C7C1C.quest_desc: [
		"Items can be placed on the Cutting Board by using them on it. It always prefers receiving items from the off-hand, allowing players to hold their ingredients there while holding the tool in their main hand, processing the stack simply by holding the use button."
		""
		"When the correct tool is used on a valid item, it will be broken down into 1-4 different outputs, which are swiped sideways. Outputs always fly to the direction opposite to the Cutting Board's handle, allowing them to be collected by an item-capturing block, such as a Hopper or Basket. The tool receives 1 point of damage for each processed item."
	]
	quest.2FEC85DD348C7C1C.quest_subtitle: "The Cutting Board is a workstation where players can break down one item into many outputs, by using a valid tool on it."
	quest.2FF97DE5D1B0F727.quest_subtitle: "Discover a Fortress of the Undead"
	quest.3033326B182BE9B3.quest_desc: [
		"The Rotary Condensentrator is used for converting substances between liquid and gaseous forms at a rate of 1:1. "
		""
		"It has two modes: Decondensentrating, which turns Liquids into Gases, and Condensentrating, which turns Gases into Liquids. "
		""
		""
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"Liquid → Gas"
		"Water → Water Vapor"
		"Liquid Sulfuric Acid → Sulfuric Acid"
		"Liquid Hydrogen Chloride → Hydrogen Chloride"
		"Liquid Oxygen → Oxygen"
		"Liquid Hydrogen → Hydrogen"
		"Liquid Ethylene → Ethylene"
		"Liquid Chlorine → Chlorine"
		"Liquid Sulfur Dioxide → Sulfur Dioxide"
		"Liquid Sulfur Trioxide → Sulfur Trioxide"
		"Brine → Gaseous Brine"
		"Liquid Lithium → Lithium"
		""
		"and the opposite is true in Condensentrating mode. "
	]
	quest.304E1101C597A163.quest_desc: ["Botany Pots is a mod that lets you grow crops, flowers, and other kind of plants in customizxable pots. Each pot is like a miniature farm, just place add soil, plant the seed, and watch them grow!"]
	quest.304E1101C597A163.title: "Botany Pots"
	quest.307CEB5B2CAB719E.quest_desc: [
		"A Campfire Pot is a utility block which is used to create various food-related items when placed on a Campfire."
		""
		"In addition to its crafting slots, it features three Seasoning slots, which act as modifiers to certain recipes."
		""
		"Campfire pots also allow some early-game Brewing recipes, allowing for pre-Nether Potions at the cost of lower efficiency. "
	]
	quest.307CEB5B2CAB719E.title: "Campfire Pot"
	quest.30C78663D8EC4B91.quest_desc: ["Evolve a Spewpa in the Nether"]
	quest.30E915732BC23F46.quest_desc: [
		"&dPondering&r is an in-game guide system that allows the player to quickly get information about Create blocks."
		""
		"An item can be &4Pondered&r by hovering over it and holding \"&6W&r\" until the bar below the item is filled up. This displays an animated infographic about the item being pondered."
		""
		"The full &6Ponder Index&r can be accessed through the Create menu by clicking the Engineer's Goggles icon in the pause menu."
	]
	quest.30E915732BC23F46.quest_subtitle: "Check it out right now. It's awesome I promise!"
	quest.30E915732BC23F46.title: "Don't forget to &nHold&r &4[w]&r &nto&r &6Ponder&r &nto learn more!&r"
	quest.310CF42911589333.quest_desc: ["The Quiver can hold a large amount of arrows that can be quick selected."]
	quest.311BF65CA07A4E45.quest_desc: ["Expanded Storage you can wear on your back. Default access key is &zb&r"]
	quest.311BF65CA07A4E45.title: "Backpacks"
	quest.3159092045C399BB.quest_subtitle: "Title Wipe"
	quest.3159092045C399BB.title: "Blank Slate"
	quest.31E7C56ABBA6A7B2.quest_desc: ["This combination allows your mount to be a lot more agile during travels. Since mounts eat a large volume of feed, the item does not need to be contained in a Bowl, saving some inventory space."]
	quest.32DBEE5C8FF78CA8.title: "Fairy Garden Roll"
	quest.337BABA052DA1E0E.quest_subtitle: "Find all the new Villages(11)"
	quest.33871879DC31D806.quest_desc: ["Launches you into the air when powered, or if you land on it from a high place"]
	quest.345ABAA111A42756.quest_desc: [
		"- Axolotls: Simply feed a wild axolotl a few tropical fish to tame them. They can be made to sit, wander and follow like all the other tameable mobs. Note that axolotls are by default very slow on land, dry out and have low health"
		""
		"- Foxes: To get a tame fox, you need to breed two wild foxes with sweet berries and wait for it to grow up. Note that no matter how tame foxes are, they'll still want to kill any chickens and (untamed) rabbits they can see."
		""
		"- Rabbits: To tame a rabbit, feed it several Hay Bales. Rabbits only have 3 health by default and usually (see: Sinister Carrot) cannot attack. However, to make them useful we have reintroduced another removed feature: rabbits scare off ravagers."
		""
		"- Frogs: you can tame them with a few spider eyes. Frogs can be made to stay, follow or wander like the other pets, and will come to their owner's defense."
	]
	quest.346F409769E670CA.quest_desc: ["A particle defying nature and is the result of decades of research. This is the Logic of the Master Ball. Caculcating every outcome and determining a future where failure is not an option."]
	quest.346F409769E670CA.quest_subtitle: "The Core"
	quest.347C4ABF9BCB62A2.quest_desc: ["A small early-game shulker box that can only hold 5 items. Carry too many in your inventory and you get slowed down"]
	quest.34822FE2F5408EE5.quest_desc: [
		"When held, the &6Extendo Grip&r increases the player's reach by 4 blocks and increases knockback. When held in the offhand, these bonuses are retained."
		""
		"When the &6Extendo Grip&r is used to break blocks, place blocks, or hit mobs, it will lose durability regardless of whether it's in the main or offhand unless used in conjunction with a filled Copper Backtank, in which case the tank's air is used instead."
		""
		"Much like super glue and sandpaper, it can be enchanted with unbreaking and mending books."
		""
		"To use a tool/item in it, put the item in your offhand and hold the &6Extendo Grip&r (the extendo grip can also be in the offhand)"
	]
	quest.3483F642D8F5D294.quest_desc: ["The gearbox is a simple block that relays rotation between 4 of its faces while reversing straight connections."]
	quest.34D365CFB0A240F9.quest_desc: [
		"&n&9Controlling Rotation Speed&r&r"
		""
		"For the &6Rotation Speed Controller&r to work, it must be paired with a &4Large Cogwheel&r. The Rotation Speed Controller, when powered by the Large Cogwheel, outputs any desired speed of rotational force from its sides. "
		""
		"It also does the opposite; when powered from its sides, it controls the speed of the Large Cogwheel."
		""
		"The rotation speed and direction can be changed in the &4Value Settings Screen&r at the front or the back of the machine. The speed can be set to any non-zero integer from -256 to 256."
	]
	quest.34D365CFB0A240F9.quest_subtitle: "Allows the player to precisely control rotational speed."
	quest.352903E9464612E7.quest_subtitle: "Champ"
	quest.352903E9464612E7.title: "Iron Chef"
	quest.353D02DBA1D6DA0C.title: "Creative Energy Cell"
	quest.3580AAEF1770B0F1.quest_desc: ["The &6Spout&r can be filled with up to 1 bucket of any one liquid via &5Fluid Pipes&r. It will then spout the fluid at appropriate items that pass under it via a &2Conveyor Belt&r or &2Depot.&r The spout takes 1 second to process an item regardless of the amount of fluid used, though delay between fills may be cause by the time it takes the spout to fill back up."]
	quest.3580AAEF1770B0F1.quest_subtitle: "Used for filling liquid containers such as bottles or buckets, or crafting with liquids."
	quest.35DC92C0C706A260.quest_desc: [
		"Items created with Tetra will have several different ways of leveling with use or construction."
		""
		"Synergy is the most basic form of leveling up a tool that comes during construction. The inclusion of the same head twice (double head pickaxe and axe for example) will give special bonuses to the tool. These special bonuses can be checked in the holosphere."
		""
		"Settling occurs per tool part with use. When a part becomes settled it will grant bonuses to the tool such as increased integrity, though if you remove the part you will lose the bonus. There are some upgrades that never settle so don't expect everything to."
		""
		"Finally, Honing also occurs with further use of a tool with stable parts. Certain parts will become honed with use (can be checked by holding shift and hovering over the tool) where they will be able to have additional unique upgrades applied to them at a workbench. This is to encourage you to keep using and upgrading your tools. You will lose the Honing of a part by removing it so be careful and plan your upgrades."
	]
	quest.35DC92C0C706A260.title: "Tool Leveling"
	quest.360A14ED6EBA64D4.quest_subtitle: "Discover every biome(49)"
	quest.36157D5059479273.quest_subtitle: "Gather every sapling from a jungle or variants"
	quest.3693C3F67BD59401.quest_desc: ["This combination allows wolves to catch up a lot more easily with you or nimble opponents, as well as last longer in battle."]
	quest.36EB24E17624949C.quest_desc: ["Found via Mushroom Fields biome"]
	quest.3746FD072D591CBB.quest_subtitle: "Upgrade a Mallet and use it to break open a Geode at a Workbench"
	quest.375CE372A0A91A71.quest_desc: [
		"When this treatise is near a workbench any major module made of scale will do extra damage and have better efficiency."
		""
		"Can be bought from leatherworker villagers."
	]
	quest.376C01998E33A655.title: "Raid Pouch"
	quest.3770B7298AFF38A4.quest_desc: [
		"The most basic and cheapest way of transferring rotational force is the shaft. This will relay rotation in a straight line to all connected shafts."
		""
		"Shafts also come in a encased variant, they have the same functionality, just look a bit different"
	]
	quest.38B08A136E92B917.quest_desc: [
		"When this treatise is near a workbench any major module made of skin (leather) will do extra damage and have better efficiency."
		""
		"Can be bought from leatherworker villagers."
	]
	quest.38F2496537D730C2.quest_desc: [
		"The Trainer Card will help you to keep track of your progress, find information about trainers and to locate the next key trainer to increase your level cap, when they spawn nearby."
		""
		""
		"You can level beyond the suggested level cap but beware. The Trainers match your level. First challenge is level 15."
	]
	quest.38F2496537D730C2.title: "Trainer Card"
	quest.38F85C0E61804F31.quest_desc: ["https://wiki.aidancbrady.com/wiki/Ore_Processing"]
	quest.38F85C0E61804F31.quest_subtitle: "Pictures included"
	quest.38FB5D47AC4952B6.title: "Trans Lives Matter"
	quest.395D7546D60AC9DC.quest_desc: ["The Advanced Solar Generator only produces full power during a clear day. It produces no power during night time, and only 20% of what it would otherwise during a rain."]
	quest.39CFF60D8B06E5A3.quest_desc: ["Can be socketed into a tool then tweaked in the tweaking menu of the workbench to change the level of a tools abilities."]
	quest.3A056B1F1F1D6D44.quest_desc: [
		"This tier quadruples ingot yield. It uses the Thermal Evaporation Plant multi-block structure, Chemical Injection Chamber, and all machines from the previous tier. "
		""
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"The steps of the process for this tier are as follows:"
		""
		"    Silk Touch Ore + Hydrogen Chloride → Chemical Injection Chamber → 4 Shards"
		"    4 Shards + Oxygen → Purification Chamber → 4 Clumps"
		"    4 Clumps → Crusher → 4 Dirty Dusts → Enrichment Chamber → 4 Dusts → Energized Smelter → 4 Ingots"
		""
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"The chain to make Hydrogen Chloride is self-sustaining, and breaks into 3 individual loops:"
		""
		"    Water → Electric Pump → Thermal Evaporation Plant → Brine → Electrolytic Separator → Sodium and Chlorine"
		"    Salt → Chemical Oxidizer → Gaseous Brine → Rotary Condensentrator → Brine → Electrolytic Separator → Sodium and Chlorine"
		"    Hydrogen (from water electrolysis) and Chlorine → Chemical Infuser → Hydrogen Chloride"
	]
	quest.3A056B1F1F1D6D44.quest_subtitle: "4x Ore Processing"
	quest.3A0875C14DD99C9D.quest_desc: [
		"PokéNav that allows you to find out which Pokémon may appear in the area you are currently in, the chances of them appearing, and the factors that influence their appearance. "
		""
		"The mod also allows you to track appearing Pokémon using a three-dimensional arrow or a radar item called PokéFinder"
	]
	quest.3A768E3EC544BDE4.quest_desc: [
		"The Toolbelt will allow you to have different addons such as carrying extra tools, items, and potions. It is curios compatible in the belt slot."
		""
		"Check your keybinds to be able to use the quick access function or access key."
	]
	quest.3A768E3EC544BDE4.title: "Rope Toolbelt"
	quest.3AD7DA2F942BC94F.title: "The Bumblezone"
	quest.3AED592F764C56FC.title: "Void Worm Blade"
	quest.3C1D930613F170F9.quest_desc: ["When added to the Forge Hammer it allows upgrades made with the hammer to have better stats."]
	quest.3C6CA584F934B8B9.quest_subtitle: "Discover a Monster Room"
	quest.3CD71C058A0A5126.title: "Enchant Anything"
	quest.3D63DAC3E66CF7D8.quest_subtitle: "Use a Bolt to bind a tool or a sword, then use the tweak tab in a workbench to change the stats of the item"
	quest.3D795EA23FA1D86E.quest_desc: ["An invisible item frame for showing your items!"]
	quest.3D9861B06498EF9D.quest_desc: [
		"&6&nClutch&r&r"
		""
		"The Clutch &4stops&r outgoing &4rotation&r when a redstone signal is applied."
		""
		"&6&nGearshift&r&r"
		""
		"The Gearshift &9reverses&r outgoing &9Rotational Force&r when a Redstone signal is applied."
		""
		"&6&nEncased Chain Drive&r&r"
		""
		"The Encased Chain Drive is a block that can &2transfer rotation&r much like the Mechanical Belt."
		""
		"Encased chain drives may be placed side by side either vertically or horizontally to form a chain passing rotational power among all the blocks. The blocks must touch on their sides (not axis to side) and be in a single straight line to form a chain. The axes of the encased chain drives may be all parallel or blocks can be rotated to orient the axis perpendicularly. Encased chain drives can also pass rotational power through their rotating axis, but this is not a continuation of the same chain."
	]
	quest.3DBFEED316353408.quest_desc: [
		"Wolves, Cats, Parrots, Axolotls, Rabbits, and Foxes now have 3 possible states when tamed: Wander, Stay and Follow."
		""
		"These can be cycled through by right clicking on the mob. Now its finally possible to have your cats and dogs wander around your house instead of being frozen in place or randomly teleport to you."
	]
	quest.3DBFEED316353408.title: "Wander, Stay, Follow"
	quest.3DC8CBEB83275A0B.quest_desc: ["This guy is really hard to find, don't bother looking for him"]
	quest.3DC8CBEB83275A0B.title: "The Rarest Trader"
	quest.3E292955FC14B413.quest_desc: [
		"There are several Labyrinths buried under the swamp. You may locate a natural entrance through a chasm or cave, or you may find the entrance in a small mound. There is more information on the Labyrinth page. Your goal is to find and slay the Minoshroom."
		""
		"Killing the Minoshroom, and eating some of his Meef Stroganoff will allow you to enter the Fire Swamp without being burnt. "
	]
	quest.3E292955FC14B413.quest_subtitle: "Swamp"
	quest.3E292955FC14B413.title: "Labyrinth"
	quest.3E31CABE22FEB919.title: "Executioner Blade"
	quest.3E87ADA2C0121147.quest_desc: [
		"Visit MineColonies wiki for more info:"
		"https://wiki.minecolonies.ldtteam.com"
	]
	quest.3E87ADA2C0121147.title: "For More Info....."
	quest.3EDCE472AFDF6BCF.quest_desc: ["A Sandy Mulch makes the Berry Tree act like it's in an Arid biome for an infinite duration. "]
	quest.3F5E565905E0C557.quest_subtitle: "Simple Gym Alternative"
	quest.3FF4D9E0E70F84E5.quest_desc: ["Kill a Ghast in the Overworld."]
	quest.4032D56BB750AAE8.quest_desc: ["The Pickaxe head is.... a pickaxe head. It allows you to mine just like you would expect it to do."]
	quest.4097AA19C7C362A2.quest_desc: ["A condensed, coiled resistor capable of converting electrical energy directly into heat energy. "]
	quest.40ACAB8E9074A452.quest_desc: ["Evolve a Spewpa in the Deep Dark"]
	quest.411C920C7FC571B6.quest_subtitle: "The Lifeblood"
	quest.414ABFFA4C532F7D.quest_desc: [
		"/pokehunt status — Show current target (species + nature or any)."
		""
		"/pokehunt start <species> <nature> — Start a manual hunt. (op)"
		""
		"Species can be charmander or cobblemon:charmander"
		""
		"/pokehunt stop — Stop the current hunt. (op)"
		""
		"/pokehunt claim <index> — Winner-only button handler for rewards."
	]
	quest.41C1DB355B80F76A.quest_subtitle: "Begin Pastel"
	quest.41F41D6F94982616.quest_desc: ["To create the Cow in a Jar, you have to drop an anvil on a cow who is standing on top of a Milk Jar. The Cow in a Jar will then slowly fill up its jar with milk "]
	quest.41F55DC1E5D636DE.quest_desc: [
		"/warp <name> - Teleports to a warp"
		""
		"/listwarps - Lists all warps"
	]
	quest.41F55DC1E5D636DE.quest_subtitle: "Server Waypoints"
	quest.42C98E7C6671B2E0.quest_desc: ["The Portable Teleporter is a player kept teleportation device. It can store power and like all Mekanism teleporters, energy drain increases with the distance the player teleports to. Right-clicking with this device in hand will open a GUI similar to that of the Teleporter Portal, allowing instant travel to any Teleporter Portals that the player has set up. The Portable Teleporter is capable of multidimensional travel. "]
	quest.42FC3B6B6A3DEF7F.quest_desc: ["The Chargepad is a wireless electric charging station. Any rechargeable items you have in your inventory will be charged while standing on it. "]
	quest.436215EE7120BF8E.quest_desc: [
		"The Milk Jar is a jar that can hold up to 8 buckets of milk. Milk Jars in your kitchen will supply milk to any recipes that require it. "
		""
		"Right click with a bucket of milk to put milk into the Milk Jar. You can also right click with an empty bucket to take milk out of the jar. "
	]
	quest.43A7E2940F0195CA.quest_desc: [
		"Cardboard Box is used for boxing up other blocks to move them, preserving the inventory while being moved. By right clicking it on any block, tank, chest or machine, you wrap it in this protective box that you can break while still preserving everything about that block, tank, chest or machine. This includes its inventory, orientation, installed upgrades, and more, and should work with any block from any mod. "
		""
		"You can later place it safely into the world. Sneak right-click to unwrap a box, causing the Cardboard Box to drop as an item. "
	]
	quest.43E36BC3E6A84780.quest_desc: ["Minecolonies is probably the slowest on this list and the hardest to get into. However its extremely productive the more you put into it. "]
	quest.43E414A246A05B0E.quest_subtitle: "Enter a Bastion Remnant"
	quest.44018815222E8CA9.quest_desc: ["can place blocks from a distance!"]
	quest.447D1005B0881D70.quest_desc: [
		"Using a Knife on grassy plants will yield Straw, a useful building and composting material. Early on, it's best used to craft some Ropes."
		""
	]
	quest.44875B6FA3D7CE74.quest_desc: ["Shields will be the best way to protect yourself outside of armor."]
	quest.44B2156EBA384F69.title: "Punch Trees"
	quest.4528C4656D892D07.title: "Barrels"
	quest.4543AC5C60608FA2.quest_desc: [
		"Mekanism is a high-tech automation mod that provides advanced machinery, multi-tiered ore processing (up to 5x yields), and complex energy systems. "
		""
		"It focuses on a unified, scientific experience featuring everything from jetpacks and digital miners to massive fusion reactors and modular power-suits."
	]
	quest.4543AC5C60608FA2.title: "Mekanism"
	quest.455AC472579E7786.quest_desc: ["Belt straps allow the carrying and quick selection of multiple tools or items."]
	quest.4568A8D52BA57B16.quest_desc: [
		"Similar to the Universal Cable, the Thermodynamic Conductor is Mekanism's way of transferring power in the form of heat (essentially a heat pipe)."
		""
		"Transfer is lossy, depending on the biome the conductor is in. Warmer biomes have a higher transfer efficiency (i.e., less heat is lost), while colder biomes are lower (i.e., more heat is lost). "
	]
	quest.4568A8D52BA57B16.quest_subtitle: "Heat Transfer"
	quest.45DC77C714EB294E.title: "Katana Blade"
	quest.461ACF01D4F2D540.title: "Win 5 Raids"
	quest.470CCDDFA6E1CBBB.quest_subtitle: "Seek out the Trainer Association to start a journey of your choice."
	quest.47123B901690686D.title: "Saber Blade"
	quest.47996E93799B3383.quest_subtitle: "Ride a Strider with a Warped Fungus on a stick"
	quest.47A879AED7CD6345.quest_desc: [
		"A lot of Create's machines need to be powered to operate. This power can be called rotational force or just Rotation."
		""
		"There are a couple different components that can create this rotational force in one way or another, they are called Generators. Just generation alone won't get you very far though, it still has to be relayed to the desired machines."
		""
		"There is a variety of different blocks in Create that can achieve just that. Best is play around with each component to familiarize yourself with its abilities. It is important to know the options when having to deal with complex connection tasks in a potentially less forgiving environment."
		""
		"Multiple generators can be connected together in order achieve a greater Capacity score for the attached kinetic network. When attaching new generators to running components, it is important that the added generator rotates in the same direction as the component it is attached to. When connecting two kinetic blocks with incompatible direction of rotation, you'll notice that the blocks just break. However, trouble-shooting this will be quite straight-forward - all you need to do is to include a means of reversing the rotation between the generator and the rest"
	]
	quest.47C39243DFD2A7AB.quest_subtitle: "All-in-One Tool"
	quest.4890308F6A77A05C.quest_subtitle: "Loot a chest in a Bastion Remnant"
	quest.490BB3543183E1DA.quest_subtitle: "Have a level 5 Town Hall"
	quest.49A7EEC4DA3E93CB.quest_desc: ["A Crafting Table would shatter under the pressure. Construct a grand 5x5 assembly line."]
	quest.49A7EEC4DA3E93CB.quest_subtitle: "The Crafting Table"
	quest.49A86430536744AD.title: "Eternal Starlight"
	quest.4A7379ED5BC0C161.quest_desc: ["A very nice volcanic stone hammer, stonger than most metals."]
	quest.4A79883566D5B449.quest_desc: ["You will need a frame capable of withstanding sub-atomic stress"]
	quest.4A79883566D5B449.quest_subtitle: "The Frame"
	quest.4A7E5D7579F5EF58.title: "Lets Go Eevee"
	quest.4A7FDA76D501244A.quest_desc: [
		"Beneath the Dark Forest (and sometimes the surrounding areas) lay the fallen Strongholds of the Twilight Knights. The lower levels of the strongholds are completely sealed, and before you enter, you will have to complete a small initiation ceremony. You will have to find a specific room in the upper ruins of the stronghold. The room contains a Trophy Pedestal and a shallow pit blocked by Stronghold Shields. Placing a trophy from one of the previous bosses on the pedestal will remove the shield and allow access to the lower levels."
		""
		"Once inside the main part of the stronghold, you will eventually have to find the Knight Phantoms to proceed. Sending the phantoms to their final rest will make the strange devices of the Dark Tower obey you. "
	]
	quest.4A7FDA76D501244A.quest_subtitle: "Dark Forest"
	quest.4A7FDA76D501244A.title: "Twilight Knight Stronghold"
	quest.4BCA960017B0992C.quest_subtitle: "Locate a Bastille"
	quest.4BEC7C7000CA0094.quest_desc: [
		"- Axe efficieny can be bought from fletcher villagers. "
		""
		"- Hammer efficieny can be bought from metal working villagers."
		""
		"- Cut efficiency can be bought from leatherworker villagers."
	]
	quest.4BEC7C7000CA0094.quest_subtitle: "Can be bought from villagers"
	quest.4BEC7C7000CA0094.title: "Treatise: Tool efficiency"
	quest.4C32738CB07377F2.quest_subtitle: "Get the Egg"
	quest.4C7D95C00F276FC9.quest_desc: ["Can be used to make a very powerful digging tool."]
	quest.4CACF5333840984D.quest_desc: ["The Chemical Crystallizer turns Clean Slurry into Crystals, Lithium into Lithium Dust and Antimatter into Antimatter Pellet."]
	quest.4D34DB2A28C1B0DA.quest_desc: ["Can be attached to a Forge Hammer or a Transfer Unit to increase its efficiency."]
	quest.4D56A1A3E3A1202E.quest_desc: [
		"Collar Tags are the conduit for pet enchantments."
		""
		"Like a nametag, these collar tags can be renamed in an anvil and used on a mob to rename it (unlike a nametag, this is only for animals that are your pets). However, their real use is that they can be enchanted"
		""
		"These collars can then be placed on a tamed pet of yours by interacting with it. To get the enchanted collar back, you can simply swap it with any other collar, including an unenchanted one. You can view a pet's enchants by sneaking and looking at them."
	]
	quest.4D56A1A3E3A1202E.title: "Collar Tag and Enchanting"
	quest.4D7997F821600BF2.quest_desc: ["Can only be activated by players."]
	quest.4DFD8DABC116C853.quest_desc: [
		"When powered by &oRotational Force&r, an &6Encased Fan&r creates an air stream that extends several blocks in front of it. This air stream &9pushes&r entities away from the fan or pulls entities towards it depending on the direction of the rotation that the fan receives. Powering an &6Encased Fan&r with faster rotational force will cause its air stream to be stronger and faster."
		""
		"Items will always be pushed, but mobs or players won't be pushed until the Fan is running at least 4 rpm."
		""
		"&n&9Vertical Item Transport&r&r"
		"Fans can also be used to push or pull items through &5Chutes.&r Items inserted into the chutes will be pushed/pulled by the fan."
		""
		"&n&9Bulk Item Processing&r&r"
		""
		"When the air stream of an Encased Fan passes through certain blocks, the air stream downstream will apply the respective processing to items."
	]
	quest.4DFD8DABC116C853.quest_subtitle: "Used for moving entities, vertical transport of items, Bulk Washing, Bulk Blasting, Bulk Haunting, and Bulk Smoking."
	quest.4E0D9C4E9CA4EF31.quest_desc: ["Disenchant items and collect &aexperience&r as liquid."]
	quest.4E0D9C4E9CA4EF31.quest_subtitle: "Create Enchantment Industry Addon"
	quest.4E0D9C4E9CA4EF31.title: "Create Enchantment Industry"
	quest.4E54B4188FA945D7.quest_desc: ["Blocks that can be wirelessly linked to other Gym Blocks and emit a redstone signal when the connected block (or blocks - supports AND/OR logic) are completed."]
	quest.4E609BA887E082A1.quest_desc: ["Mulch is an item that is used to give berry trees a certain boost. "]
	quest.4F0E9E63C8FCFD67.quest_desc: ["The Metallurgic Infuser is the first step in the Mekanism tech tree. The Metallurgic Infuser is a machine used in the production of &8Steel Ingots&r, &6Bronze Ingot&r, &4Enriched Alloy&r, and &0Obsidian Ingots&r. "]
	quest.4F20540765A93D77.quest_subtitle: "Discover a Battle Tower"
	quest.4F2EAF7F65E14680.quest_subtitle: "Have 50 citizens"
	quest.4F97FA3B5C6831CB.title: "Archelogy"
	quest.4FA95EFF9717CA59.quest_desc: ["The Jetpack is an item that allows the player to fly, equippable in the chestplate slot. It uses Hydrogen gas as a fuel, of which it can store up to 24,000 mB. "]
	quest.502517E2C3BCCC96.quest_desc: [
		"The portal can be assembles in any shape and size you want, the image above is just the minimum size requirement and the portal can be made in many different shapes and sizes. The portal functions as long as the following conditions are met:"
		"1.)   The frame is made out of Grass, Dirt, Podzol, Mycelium, etc."
		"2.)   On top of the grass are flowers, mushrooms, leaves, plants, etc."
		"3.)   The frame must be completely filled with water."
		""
		"When setup throw in a &bdiamond!&r"
	]
	quest.502517E2C3BCCC96.quest_subtitle: "The Portal"
	quest.502517E2C3BCCC96.title: "Twilight Forest"
	quest.503765686BCC67C1.quest_desc: ["A Buckler shield will give you a passive armor bonus when hend in your offhand but cannot be used to actively block."]
	quest.506F2EE769DE5AFA.quest_subtitle: "Minecolonies"
	quest.506F2EE769DE5AFA.title: "Repopulating the Homestead"
	quest.507FC5E479A1EFFA.quest_desc: [
		"The &6Toolbox&r can hold up to 256 items per slot and has 8 slots. The inventory is retained when picked up. Players can press the toolbox keybind (Alt by default) to access the toolbox inventory from up to 10 blocks away. Retrieving an item in this manner causes a gold border with a red indicator on the top and bottom to appear. This &4red&r indicator becomes dark red when the toolbox is out of range."
		""
		"While the player is in range of the toolbox, items will also be refilled. "
		""
		"If multiple toolboxes are in range, the player can choose which toolbox to access. Players can choose to stack all matching items into the toolbox by clicking the \"Return items\" button in the interface."
	]
	quest.50DF8B73D579D418.quest_subtitle: "Gather every sapling from a dark forest or variants"
	quest.514ADF2A6EE7538C.quest_desc: ["A Heater shield can only be used for so long before going on cooldown for further use."]
	quest.5174D7892CC4EC9C.quest_desc: ["emits redstone signal when a key is used on it. The key can be renamed so only that key can be used."]
	quest.5196E1C378F3EDF6.quest_desc: [
		"The &6Steam Engine&r is a block that provides Rotational Force. "
		""
		"It outputs the highest &cStress Unit&r (SU) capacity of all the survival-mode power-generating blocks. "
		""
		"It converts the pressure caused by &4heating&r &9Water&r in a Fluid Tank into Rotational Force, allowing for large scale item production and multiple contraptions."
	]
	quest.51B645F179FB38C5.quest_desc: ["The Crusher crushes, among other things, clumps into Dirty Dusts, Ingots into dusts and Biomatter into Bio Fuel. "]
	quest.51DAE2F60025F735.quest_desc: ["The brain of the gym. Link your gym blocks to the controller to keep track of them and to allow your gym to be reset upon completion!"]
	quest.52911A04226B3393.title: "Creative Fluid Tank"
	quest.52B54E2CE151772D.quest_desc: [
		"When this treatise is near a workbench any major module made of bone will do extra damage and have better efficiency."
		""
		"Can be bought from butcher villagers."
	]
	quest.533F93A6D4914D2F.quest_desc: [
		"The Rope Pulley can extend downwards 256 blocks before stopping (Configurable.) It is most commonly used for excavating or simple elevators. The rope of the pulley is climbable while disassembled."
		""
		"Use Block Attachment Utilities to push more blocks. Rope Pulleys directly above the Contraption at the same level of the main Rope Pulley will synchronize with the main pulley. Synchronized Pulleys do not require Rotational Force."
		""
		"The Rope Pulley's current length can be monitored with a Threshold Switch."
	]
	quest.53724A1FE29BFB20.quest_desc: ["Bows can be upgraded into a number of unique forms with their own advantages."]
	quest.53724A1FE29BFB20.quest_subtitle: "Upgrade a bow in a workbench"
	quest.538F41CD0B583574.quest_desc: ["Spears are a basic weapon that can easily be made."]
	quest.53C3ED6F7249424E.quest_desc: ["Bamboo spikes are useful traps to protect you base from mobs. They can be tipped with potion effects!"]
	quest.53D50C96CF52CEA4.quest_desc: ["Fishing with a Poké Rod whilst using a Master Ball bobber. Has the same other conditions as a regular Whiscash."]
	quest.540B55BEFF0879E3.quest_desc: ["The Iron Sheet is the sheet variant of Iron."]
	quest.54438DD2E091D193.quest_subtitle: "Biome Searching"
	quest.54438DD2E091D193.title: "Nature's Compass"
	quest.5445EFE23925AAB0.quest_subtitle: "Power Demand: High"
	quest.54511C4D1AD2151B.quest_desc: [
		"This machine uses energy to extract dusts out of certain blocks and ores, making it essential to producing different kinds of tools. "
		""
		"Not to be mistaken with the Crusher, this machine is the pulverizer equivalent in other mods. "
	]
	quest.557DE4B851A81D4A.quest_subtitle: "Hire 8 guards"
	quest.5594C5833447A6EC.quest_desc: [
		"The Display Board must be powered at an RPM of 30+ to display text."
		""
		"Use a Clipboard or a Name Tag on a line of the Display Board to write the item's contents to it. "
		""
		"Each Display Board block can hold 2 lines of text. Lines can be erased using an empty hand. "
		""
		"Lines can also be colored by using Dyes or illuminated with Glow Inc Sacs."
		""
		"Display Boards can be expanded up to 32 blocks above, below, and to either side, allowing a maximum Display Board size of 32x32."
	]
	quest.55AF1779E7AE28A7.quest_desc: ["When consumed, it will remove a single random negative effect from the player, keeping positive ones untouched. This provides a simple use for Cocoa Beans in difficult, risky trips."]
	quest.55C9DDEEE3C67A76.title: "Questing Ram"
	quest.569EA5826498AEA2.quest_desc: [
		"With any luck, planting the Magic Beans in a patch of Uberous Soil will send a beanstalk spiraling up into the bottom of the clouds above. Up on the cloud, you will find a cottage with several Giants patrolling nearby. Take what treasure you can, but you will need the Giant's Pickaxe to continue."
		""
		"With the Giant's Pickaxe you can open the huge obsidian vault in the center of the Troll Caves. Inside the vault, you will find the Lamp of Cinders. The power of the lamp can burn the thorns in the nearby Thornlands. "
	]
	quest.569EA5826498AEA2.title: "Cloud Cottages"
	quest.56B6FCA3F5434E3A.quest_desc: [
		"Right-click a &6Train Track&r, then place the Station within 15 blocks of the track. Stations can be placed on any Track so long as it isn't occupied by a &6Train Signal&r or &6Train Observer&r, however it can only create &5Trains&r if placed on a straight Track, and Bogeys may only be placed on a 3 block long straight track."
		""
		"&n&6Train Creation&r&r"
		""
		"&5Trains&r can only be created on straight tracks; a Station cannot begin an assembly on a curved or diagonal track, and Bogeys may only be placed on at least 3 straight tracks in a row. Starting behind the station and going backwards, &5Trains&r are created from the front to the back. An assembly track can be up to 128 blocks long."
		""
		"&5Trains&r cannot be assembled or disassembled automatically in unmodified Create, but the 3rd party addon &nCreate Steam n' Rails&r allows for this. With this addon loaded, A Deployer that hits a Train Station while equipped with a Wrench [via use of a Chute or alternative] will (dis)assemble the parked train."
		""
		"&n&6Door Controls&r&r"
		""
		"In the &6Station's&r interface, the behavior of Sliding Doors on arriving trains can be decided. The options are Open All Doors, North, East, West, and South Side Only, or Keep Doors Closed."
		""
		"&n&6Train Scheduling&r&r"
		""
		"Conductors can be instructed to navigate between Stations using &5Train Schedules&r. Notably, * can be used as a wildcard character when instructing conductors to navigate to stations. If a Train is scheduled to arrive at Station*, it can arrive at either Station1 or Station2 depending on which is more accessible at the time."
	]
	quest.56B6FCA3F5434E3A.quest_subtitle: "Train Stations are used to create, disassemble, and guide Trains."
	quest.56D3BC7D09F900CA.quest_desc: [
		"Rich Soil is an enhanced type of dirt, more fertile and durable to the elements."
		""
		"Rich Soil cannot be directly crafted. To make it, you must craft Organic Compost and place it into the world, letting it decompose over time."
		""
		"Organic Compost will decompose more easily under sunlight and moisture from nearby water, but doesn't actually hydrate like farmland. It can also be gently accelerated by placing activators next to it, in a 3x3x3 area centered on itself."
		""
		"Currently, the following blocks behave as activators for Organic Compost:"
		"- Brown and Red Mushrooms, and their Colonies;"
		"- Podzol and Mycelium;"
		"- Other blocks of Organic Compost;"
		"- Rich Soil, normal or tilled."
	]
	quest.57114F4515F106CE.quest_desc: ["The Cog Block can transmit redstone vertically!"]
	quest.57114F4515F106CE.title: "VERTICAL REDSTONE?!"
	quest.573CF30AD8FA46D4.quest_desc: ["The huge vines in the Thornlands are nearly impenetrable. Fortunately the Lamp of Cinders can burn them into ash. There's nothing here to fight, but one must be careful while navigating through the Thorns. "]
	quest.573CF30AD8FA46D4.title: "Thornlands"
	quest.575CFF26D3C869A2.quest_subtitle: "Mining Dimension"
	quest.575CFF26D3C869A2.title: "Time to Rebuild"
	quest.576E37A04D699593.quest_desc: ["Cranks are used to give the exact redstone signal you want"]
	quest.576E37A04D699593.title: "The Crankonator"
	quest.5810EA8260E9E00D.quest_desc: [
		"If a Mekanism machine has a fluid and/or gas gauge, then you can use the Gauge Dropper on it. Open the machine's GUI and pick up the gauge dropper as you would if you where moving it to a different inventory slot. Hover over the gauge you wish to interact with, and then do one of the following:"
		""
		"    Left Click: Will collect up to 1000mB of the gas/fluid and store it in the dropper"
		"    Right Click: Will deposit whatever is in the dropper into the tank, if it is compatible and is of the same fluid/gas type (you can't put oxygen in a tank that has hydrogen in it, for example)."
		"    Sneak + Left Click: Will dump the entire tank."
		""
		"You can also dump the contents of the gauge dropper by selecting it in the hotbar (outside of any machinery GUI) and use Sneak + Right Click on any block. The contents will be destroyed in the process. "
	]
	quest.584398525C5EF003.quest_desc: [
		"Unlike the normal villagers you might see in the world, your colonists are a bit smarter. They’ll generally find a pretty good path to get where they want to go due to their advanced degrees in walking from Raycoms University and their RavenEyes© vision."
		""
		"As such, they’re able to move across flat ground, single-block steps, stairs, slabs, and other such blocks. They know how to open both wood and iron doors — even without any redstone input — trapdoors, and fence gates. They’ll climb up and down ladders and vines just fine as well. However, they will try to avoid going through fences, as is expected, and generally will find a way around dangerous obstacles like fire, magma, lava, cacti, and sweet berry bushes."
		""
		"- Getting Stuck"
		"But what if a colonist can’t find a path to where they want to go? What if, say, they fall in a hole and get stuck, or they’re trying to climb somewhere high up that doesn’t have any way there yet, or if they get trapped inside a wall by an overenthusiastic Builder? Not to fear! Your colonists are also slightly magical in that, if they’re stuck in one place for too long, they’ll build up enough willpower to relocate themselves forcibly to a nearby valid location and continue on their way."
		""
		"- Waypoints and Decorative Paths"
		"Waypoints are also used to guide your citizens along the right path, but whereas the pathblocks are for local pathing, waypoints are used more for long-distance pathing. Adding a waypoint onto bridges, for example, or in areas that you want citizens to traverse a little more frequently, can help them path across the colony more easily. As such, you don’t need very many waypoints: having a couple here and there where the pathing may be more difficult is plenty."
		""
		"The Builder can build waypoints if you request them with the build tool. You can find them in the under the decorative elements of the build tool."
		""
		"To remove a waypoint, place a solid block, such as dirt, on the waypoint and wait a few minutes. After a while, you can remove the block, and the waypoint should be removed."
		""
		"The build tool also includes several decorative paths as part of the schematics. These paths often include waypoints, so you can see how the professional schematics designers used them."
		"======================================================"
	]
	quest.584398525C5EF003.title: "===================Pathing System================="
	quest.589AAF1FD992CE82.quest_desc: ["Emits light based on its redstone signal."]
	quest.58C315F45BB5ACBA.quest_desc: ["When used, this will send out a feather on a string in front of you. The closest pet of yours will then try to move onto the feather to play with it. This tool is useful for getting your mob out of places it shouldn't be, like if it's stuck in a doorway or on top of a chest. It's also useful for moving a pet onto its bed so you can set its respawn point."]
	quest.58E51E027525C66D.quest_desc: [
		"Tetra includes a number of additional methods to better your tools. These schematics/treatises must be placed around a workbench in a 5x5x5 square of the space two above the workbench (so four blocks up the wall and two blocks off each side)."
		""
		"The way to find these new items are indicated in the quests."
		""
		"* Note: When you will pick up one scroll from category it will auto-complete the whole quest. So these quests are more like overview of scrolls available."
	]
	quest.58E51E027525C66D.title: "Scrolls, Schematics, and Treatises"
	quest.591A481681EEA88F.quest_desc: ["Can be added to a Forge Hammer to decrease the chance of it jamming by 50%."]
	quest.591D9D37D588E02A.quest_desc: ["The Rack, when placed on the wall in a 3x3 area behind a workbench, will allow tools placed on it (right click while holding tool) to be used in the workbench. "]
	quest.5954871D011EA31B.quest_subtitle: "Discover a Spider Cave"
	quest.596E7279DE886CA8.quest_desc: [
		"The Controller allows players to manage multiple storage blocks as if they were part of a single, unified storage multiblock."
		""
		"Storage blocks can be connected by placing them directly adjacent to the Controller or next to other storage blocks already connected to the Controller. Connections can extend up to 15 blocks in any direction."
		""
		"Additional connection options are:"
		"Using the Storage Tool to link individual storage blocks to the Controller"
		"Linking a Storage Link block, which itself can connect to multiple other storage blocks"
		"Right-clicking the Controller with a stack of items in hand places that stack into one of the connected storage blocks if a matching stack already exists there"
		"Double right-clicking the Controller deposits all matching stacks from the player’s inventory into the connected storage blocks"
	]
	quest.5A00FF06C8914743.quest_desc: [
		"The Flamethrower is a ranged weapon which uses Hydrogen gas as its fuel. It is fairly effective against mobs as it deals damage when they are directly hit with the stream and sets them on fire."
		""
		"It is most effective on large groups of mobs, where the user can hose down the entire group with fuel at a short distance."
		""
		""
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"You can switch between three fire modes using Shift + Item Mode (default M). The modes are"
		""
		"    Combat - The default mode. Damages mobs and sets them on fire. Destroys any items on the ground. Does not set fire to blocks nor damage them."
		"    Heat - Same as combat, but blocks/items that have a smelter recipe will be instantly converted into it. For example you can fire a short burst at iron ore block and a single ingot of iron will be dropped.1"
		"    Inferno - Same as combat, but blocks that the stream hits will be hit with blast damage (like with creepers, ghasts, TNT) and will usually be destroyed. Nearby blocks will be set on fire. The flames will also ignite campfires, candles and candled cakes, if they are not already lit."
	]
	quest.5A2297A4C2BB4A7B.quest_desc: ["captures small mobs like chickens"]
	quest.5A393255C66CECCE.title: "Tomahawk"
	quest.5A473AC80CE092BD.quest_desc: [
		"The Naga can be found in a courtyard adorned with a snake motif. There are very few obstacles in the Courtyard, and the Naga can just as easily break them down."
		""
		"Killing the Naga and touching one of his magical scales will allow you to enter the next area. "
	]
	quest.5A473AC80CE092BD.quest_subtitle: "Forest Boss"
	quest.5A473AC80CE092BD.title: "Naga"
	quest.5A83AFC08169CEF8.title: "Creative Energy Cube"
	quest.5A9FEBF577815E3D.quest_desc: [
		"The meat and potatoes of any gym. Right click the Spawner to mirror your current Cobblemon party (including levels, stats, movesets, and all that fun stuff) onto the block. "
		"Clicking the spawner again will cause a battleable trainer to spawn! Comes in Normal, Locked, and Leader varieties."
	]
	quest.5AFFEF0FE9E14625.quest_desc: [
		"&6Engineer's Goggles&r are a wearable item that allow the user to see more details about placed machines."
		""
		"While worn, the &6Engineer's Goggles&r will show the stress impact of the viewed machine while it is running. They will also give numbers and highlight the current rotation when looking at a Stressometer or Speedometer. Additionally, they show how much &9fluid&r is in a tank along with the total storage capacity of the tank."
		""
		"The &6Wrench&r is a tool used to rotate, dismantle and configure components"
		""
		"Using a &6Wrench&r on a component will rotate the component around the face with which you interacted."
		""
		"Using a &6Wrench&r on a component, redstone component, rail or vanilla rail variant will dismantle it and place it in your inventory. Any block which can be rotated or otherwise interacted with using right click must be dismantled while sneaking."
		""
		"&9Hovering&r over certain configurable components will allow configuration by scrolling."
		""
		"For certain components such as the Linear Chassis, ctrl can be held to configure all connected components at once."
	]
	quest.5BDE640F2D8C4C4F.quest_desc: ["The electric bow can be powered using energy and can toggle between \"fire\" mode if you want to bring out your inner arsonist."]
	quest.5BEE388BEF76C2FB.quest_subtitle: "Mob Drop Reproduction"
	quest.5BEE388BEF76C2FB.title: "Hostile Neural Networks"
	quest.5C054B01A4C3BBE6.quest_desc: ["Only drops from Respawned Dragons. Used to create a copy of an elytra"]
	quest.5C0CF307ED93BCB2.quest_subtitle: "Snowy Village"
	quest.5C0CF307ED93BCB2.title: "Visit a Snowy Beautify House"
	quest.5CD7BB02B1411B9E.quest_desc: [
		"The &6Portable Storage Interface&r is a block that allows Item Transporters to directly interact with "
		""
		"{ \"text\": \"> Contraption (click me) <\", \"underlined\": \"true\", \"clickEvent\": { \"action\": \"change_page\", \"value\": \"6AEB228D1B691E4E\" } }"
		""
		"inventories. "
		""
		"For &6Portable Storage Interfaces&r to interact they must face each other at 1 to 2 blocks apart. One interface must be on a &5Contraption&r, while the other is stationary."
		""
		"The &5Contraption&r must have an inventory such as a &4Chest&r or &9Barrel,&r while the stationary interface has something inserting or extracting directly from it, such as a &eFunnel,&r &8Chute,&r or &3Hopper.&r Inventory will then be exchanged at the rate of the inserting or extracting component."
		""
		"&5Contraptions&r will stall when interfaces meet. A Redstone signal can be applied to break off the connection."
	]
	quest.5CD7BB02B1411B9E.quest_subtitle: "&nHold&r &4[w]&r &nto&r &6Ponder&r &nto learn more!&r"
	quest.5CE7435CEEDB5F7A.quest_subtitle: "A Title for your Lordship"
	quest.5CFCFFA783EDF813.quest_subtitle: "Thanks for playing!"
	quest.5CFCFFA783EDF813.title: "Login 3 days in a row"
	quest.5D1BA4DC2B47A924.quest_desc: ["A Loamy Mulch makes the Berry Tree act like it's in a Plains biome for an infinite duration. "]
	quest.5D2A31DBC05AA661.quest_desc: [
		"The &9Crafting Blueprint&r is placed much like a Painting. It can cover up to a 3x3 area."
		""
		"- &5Right-click&r a slot to open the interface and use items to save a crafting recipe. Filters can also be used to apply multiple potential crafting recipes."
		""
		"- Outside the interface, right click the saved recipe to use available materials to craft the item. "
		""
		"- &5Shift-right-click&r to craft up to a stack of the item. Left click to delete a crafting recipe. A secondary display slot is available for each slot."
	]
	quest.5D2A31DBC05AA661.quest_subtitle: "Can be used to save crafting recipes and auto craft them easily."
	quest.5D5EF7C254842676.quest_desc: ["Type Gems are held items that increase the power of their respective move type used by 30%. This can only activate once per battle. "]
	quest.5D5EF7C254842676.title: "Gems"
	quest.5D83C19148119E36.quest_desc: [
		"Tier Installers are used to upgrade various machines into their Factory equivalent. Right-click on the machine with the Tier Installer and it will upgrade that machine to a Factory - its level (Basic, Advanced, or Elite) depending on the level of the Factory Installer used."
		""
		"Basic Tier Installers can be used on any machine that has a Factory associated with it that has not yet been turned into one. However, Advanced Tier Installers can only be used on Basic Factories, while Elite Tier Installers can only be used on Advanced Factories, and Ultimate Tier Installers can only be used on Elite Factories. "
	]
	quest.5D83C19148119E36.quest_subtitle: "Factories"
	quest.5D89C7F9261D1E74.quest_subtitle: "Find a chapter of Tools of War in a bastion remnant, or barter for one with a piglin"
	quest.5DAA545B3BC540EF.quest_desc: ["Evolve a Spewpa in the End"]
	quest.5DD1A32CAD544DCC.quest_subtitle: "Discover an Illager Corsair or an Illager Galley"
	quest.5E6179C6A1772DCF.quest_subtitle: "You're not not going to do this"
	quest.5E8C888A30151EE7.quest_desc: [
		"Mechanical Pistons are a Contraption that will collide with unmovable blocks."
		""
		"Moving Blocks"
		"To extend, the Piston must have Piston Extension Poles at the end as well as Rotational power. The maximum extension pole length is 64 blocks, and this can be changed in the Config."
		""
		"When the rotation is reversed, the piston will retract. The end must be made sticky with a Slimeball to bring the pushed blocks back with it."
		""
		"A placed Mechanical Piston can be made sticky by right-clicking it with a Slimeball."
		""
		"Multiple blocks can be pushed with the use of Block Attachment Utilities."
	]
	quest.5E9FE2866D9E8269.title: "Level 2"
	quest.5EE6C136B7D19495.quest_desc: ["The \"fan\" of this modpack, bellows blow mobs in the direction they are facing when powered."]
	quest.5FDAF21C72ADE73F.quest_desc: ["The Storage Link allows players to connect storage blocks that are not directly adjacent to the Controller or any blocks already connected to it."]
	quest.60A8B8712FF18A56.quest_desc: ["Lantern but brass"]
	quest.60D0B6B558C0123A.title: "Time Played 2h"
	quest.60F00B764C6CE1F3.quest_desc: ["This ladder can be hanging and does not have to be attached to a block if the top ladder is."]
	quest.619A52669514E850.quest_desc: [
		"Feasts are not edible directly as an item; they must be placed down as a block first. When placed, players can use (right-click) them with Bowls to serve themselves with a consumable portion."
		""
		"The existing feasts in Farmer's Delight provide 4 servings in total. Plated feasts will also leave behind leftovers in the form of a dirty plate; right-clicking or mining it will retrieve the original Bowl, and any bones or food scraps left behind."
	]
	quest.619A52669514E850.quest_subtitle: "Feasts are very large meals, which can be placed as a block to provide multiple servings to players."
	quest.6232E0EC41F931BA.quest_desc: ["The Sink is a block that you can use to add water to your recipes."]
	quest.6232E0EC41F931BA.quest_subtitle: "Infinite Water Source"
	quest.6232E0EC41F931BA.title: "Sink"
	quest.62701AA8050C475E.quest_desc: ["A Surprise Mulch increases the chances for a mutation of a Berry on the Berry Tree for 3 harvests. It can also mutate a fully grown Revival Herb into a Mental Herb, Power Herb, White Herb, or Mirror Herb. "]
	quest.628078793DF96DF5.quest_desc: ["Craft with a dye to create a colored rune. Runes change the enchantment glint color on your equipment when combined in an anvil with the enchanted item of your choice. The blank rune removes other rune colors."]
	quest.630F74D3EB24C0FE.quest_subtitle: "Protect your Gym from Mobs"
	quest.6387CCB5AE1A5C35.quest_desc: [
		"It stores 4096 non stackeable items(by default) and can only be accessed with external tools (currently) like Applied Energistics or Refined Storage external storage tools."
		""
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"This item was previously a huge source of lag. Unsure if it is today. Honestly no good solutions to storing a lot of items with NBT data. Better would be to salavge or strip the enchantments off items."
	]
	quest.64074C9DBD0F7C94.quest_desc: ["A Tower shield allows you to block indefinitely but it takes more integrity of the overall shield."]
	quest.6551184966D3FB8D.quest_desc: ["A Heavy blade will turn a sword into a Greatsword that does large sweeping attacks with a full charge attack."]
	quest.656E18F286DDF200.quest_desc: ["used to unlock lock blocks. You can put it in any curios slot."]
	quest.667B2CFFA3791D8D.title: "False Swipe"
	quest.668D5670FC32DB7D.title: "Daily Contract"
	quest.66D26625F2F9CB42.quest_desc: ["You can link drawers to it without having direct contact (Range can be extended with upgrades)"]
	quest.6732B0834301FF7B.quest_subtitle: "One of the important components for your Airship"
	quest.6732B0834301FF7B.title: "Airship Boiler"
	quest.673EFDF19FC3A0EB.title: "Sohpiscated Storage"
	quest.674C4F6C629090C7.quest_subtitle: "Discover a Nether City"
	quest.6773B0750333AA43.quest_desc: [
		"&6Trains&r are Contraptions that travel on &5Train Tracks&r. Unlike vanilla trains, Create Trains can be controlled by players riding on the train or by conductors, can go through unloaded chunks even when unmanned, and can pass through Nether Portals."
		""
		"The following are the minimum needed to create a Train:"
		""
		"- &3Train Track&r"
		"- &9Train Station&r"
		"- &5Train Casing &r"
		"- &6Train Controls&r"
		"- &2Block Attachment Utility&r"
		""
		"&n&6Assembly&r&r"
		""
		"1. Place the track and right-click it with a &5Station block&r. Place the station block near the track."
		""
		"2. Right click on the station and select \"&lCreate Train&r\" to enter assembly mode (blue flag shown on station)."
		""
		"3. Place one or more &6Train Casings&r on the track where indicated with blue. The casings will turn into bogeys (wheeled undercarriages.)"
		""
		"4. When assembled, each bogey will automatically become coupled together as part of the train. To create a carriage, build a platform around two bogeys' bases. "
		""
		"5. Place a &5Train Controls&r block facing the direction dictated by the station. This is shown as an arrow on the Station's selected track. Place another set of &5Train Controls&r facing the opposite way to make the engine bi-directional (able to travel in both directions) and place a &6Seat&r or &4Blaze Burner&r behind the controls for the driver."
		""
		"6. Use &aBlock Attachment Utilities&r such as Super Glue to connect all parts together (green highlight)."
		""
		"7. When finished, use the Station's interface to attempt to assemble the &5Train.&r"
		""
		"8. If a Train fails to assemble, an error will be shown in the Station's interface."
		""
		"9. When assembled, the &5Train&r can be named in the Station's interface."
	]
	quest.67D26DEF0E563519.quest_desc: [
		"&n&9Conveying Rotation&r&r"
		""
		"&6Cogwheels&r have three main methods of interlocking:"
		""
		"- &lTwo Cogwheels&r interlock when placed next to each other (not diagonally) and facing the same direction. When rotational force is provided to one of the cogwheels, the force will be provided to the other Cogwheel at the same speed but in the opposite direction."
		""
		"- &lTwo &nLarge&r Cogwheels&r interlock when placed perpendicular to each other, effectively changing its axis and direction, but not its speed."
		""
		"- A &nCogwheel&r and a &nLarge Cogwheel&r interlock when placed diagonally to each other and facing the same direction. The Large Cogwheel will rotate at half the speed of the Cogwheel."
		""
		"A &6cogwheel&r can also be used like a Shaft, conveying rotation from the ends of its axis. They can be stopped from doing this by applying a Casing, configurable with a &4Wrench.&r Mechanical components can be connected to each end, and several Cogwheels connected end-to-end function the same as multiple shafts would."
		""
		"&n&9Adjusting Speed&r&r"
		""
		"Using &npairs of Cogwheels&r and &nLarge Cogwheels&r, rotational speed can be easily doubled or halved using the mechanic mentioned above. It is possible to connect many pairs of Large Cogwheels and Cogwheels to apply this mechanic repeatedly, up to 256 RPM."
		""
		"A Large Cogwheel can also be connected to a &4Rotation Speed Controller&r, to adjust speed more precisely."
		""
		"&n&9Activating Components&r&r"
		""
		"Some blocks need to be powered by a &6Cogwheel&r to function. Those blocks contain a Cogwheel &nin their texture&r and can be powered by placing a Cogwheel adjacent to them or a large Cogwheel diagonally, both in the same direction as the block, like a normal Cogwheel."
	]
	quest.67D26DEF0E563519.quest_subtitle: "A basic mechanical component that relays rotation."
	quest.68339B382A047B89.quest_desc: ["These doors can be opened with hand but NOT redstone signals."]
	quest.6848C93746CC1FC0.quest_subtitle: "Locate a Pillager Camp"
	quest.685B1BCA8B0F49D2.quest_desc: ["The Wrench is used to rotate blocks already placed in the world."]
	quest.6869F99D79538222.quest_desc: [
		"A machine similar to the Mechanical Mixer or Mechanical Press, it automatically registers all cutting recipes from &5Farmer's Delight&r mod. In that sense, it is an &6automatic Cutting Board&r."
		""
		"In order to use it, the correct tool has to be placed into the machine, using Right-Click. By default, only knives and axes are allowed."
	]
	quest.68841C26A41D419B.quest_desc: ["Can be used to upgrade a quiver to automatically pull arrows from it."]
	quest.689E731ECC22F152.quest_subtitle: "Find all the new Mineshafts(14)"
	quest.6937607EAFBA92CA.quest_desc: [
		"The Interfaces must be placed facing each other at 1-2 blocks apart, one on a Contraption with &9Fluid Tanks&r and one stationary. A &9Fluid Pump&r is required to insert or extract liquid from the Contraption. To pump liquids to another tank, simply connect the stationary interface and the fluid tank with fluid pipes, although pumps are required to move the liquids."
		""
		"Contraptions will automatically stall for an Interface. A Redstone signal can be applied to break off the connection early."
	]
	quest.6937607EAFBA92CA.quest_subtitle: "Used to insert or extract from the fluid inventory of a Contraption."
	quest.6942ADE3BA8910F6.title: "Quarter Staff"
	quest.6945746FAEFCA3CE.quest_desc: [
		"Rarer version of bomb that can only be found as loot and from a special trader..."
		"More Powerful than bomb and sets mobs on fire!"
	]
	quest.6966DF5ED25C21DF.quest_desc: [
		"The &6Millstone&r is capable of applying milling recipes to any valid items inserted from above."
		""
		"A &6Millstone&r can be powered by a &5Shaft&r from below or by a Cogwheel from the side."
		""
		"There are two ways to insert items into a &6Millstone:&r"
		""
		"- &nDropping items on top of it&r: anything that can be processed will be picked up if the input buffer is empty."
		""
		"- &nHoppers, Funnels, Chutes&r, and other inserters can directly feed it items from any side."
		""
		"Once a valid item has been placed into the mill through any of the means listed above, the &6Millstone&r will begin to turn, and particles will appear around the machine. Once finished, the &6Millstone&r will not drop or output the result by itself, but there are two ways to remove processed items:"
		""
		"- Right-clicking the Millstone with an empty hand: this will manually pick up everything in the output buffer."
		""
		"- Hoppers, Funnels, Chutes, and other exporters can pull items out of the output buffer from any side."
	]
	quest.6966F57E97BB934C.quest_subtitle: "Use a workbench to restore the sweeping capabilities of the Holosphere Ccanner, the Ccanner makers it easier to find Ancient Ruins."
	quest.69A8C67963DBA7DA.quest_subtitle: "Gather every sapling from a plains or variants"
	quest.6A26B7E53FD7E9A8.quest_desc: [
		"These somewhat square-shaped hills are placed near the center of the snow forest regions. There are four natural entrances. Inside, you may find a pack of yetis, lorded over by the massive Alpha Yeti. "
		""
		"Defeating the Alpha Yeti in combat, and claiming some of his downy fur will make the Glacier available to you. "
	]
	quest.6A26B7E53FD7E9A8.quest_subtitle: "Snowy Forest"
	quest.6A26B7E53FD7E9A8.title: "Alpha Yeti"
	quest.6B297D22FA3C3DE0.quest_desc: ["The Snow Forests are protected by the semi-benign Yetis and the fearsome Winter Wolves. If you are not prepared, the extreme cold of the area will slow you down. Adventurers who have vanquished the Lich will not have to worry about this effect. "]
	quest.6B297D22FA3C3DE0.title: "Snowy Forest"
	quest.6B3F09472BAB8A09.quest_desc: [
		"The Twilight Lich can be found inside his Lich Tower, a large compound with multiple branching towers found in the forest. The Tower is protected by a spell that prevents breaking blocks and harming enemies. The only way in is to defeat the Naga."
		""
		"Killing the Lich and obtaining one of his magical scepters will open up three areas to explore next: The Swamp, The Dark Forest and The Snow Forest. "
	]
	quest.6B3F09472BAB8A09.quest_subtitle: "Forest Boss"
	quest.6B3F09472BAB8A09.title: "Twilight Lich"
	quest.6B649400E699D31F.title: "Fridge"
	quest.6BBB3BDE124D2C16.quest_desc: ["Can be added to a Forge Hammer to increase its hammer rank by 1 but it may light blocks around it on fire."]
	quest.6C177605D85DA8E2.quest_desc: [
		"The Purification Chamber uses &boxygen&r to refine Ores and shards into clumps. Each ore makes 3 clumps, whereas each shard only gives one clump."
		""
		"The oxygen can be provided externally as gas, internally with an oxygen filled Gas Tank or flint."
	]
	quest.6C27B8ECBE98B97A.quest_desc: ["Rotates blocks and mobs standing on it"]
	quest.6C27B8ECBE98B97A.title: "How the tables have turned..."
	quest.6C68FB7EEA0AB95B.quest_desc: [
		"The Storage Tool performs various functions, including linking, locking, and toggling the visibility of storage block properties such as locks, counts, tiers, upgrades, and more."
		""
		"General Functionality:"
		""
		"The Storage Tool can operate on individual storage blocks or on all storage blocks connected to a Controller:"
		"Right-clicking a storage block applies the action to that block only."
		"Right-clicking a Controller applies the action to all connected storage blocks."
		""
		"Use &bSneak + Scroll Wheel&r to switch between the Storage Tool's modes."
	]
	quest.6CE12F9EBD63ABFA.quest_desc: ["Emits a redstone signal when looked at."]
	quest.6D179594F4C5F517.quest_subtitle: "Find a gilding scroll in a nether fortress"
	quest.6D27F4E066C09950.quest_desc: ["The next phase of your adventures takes place in the Swamp. The swamp is infested with a haze of mosquitoes, and you will have to have defeated the Lich in order to resist the swamp sickness. "]
	quest.6D27F4E066C09950.title: "Swamp"
	quest.6D677805996BDA93.quest_desc: [
		"I'll be your short and basic guide in a beautiful world of Create!"
		""
		"&nHold&r &4[w]&r &nto&r &6Ponder&r &nto learn more!&r"
		""
		"You can also access the Ponder Index from your Esc menu!"
		""
		"You can also always check Youtube for more detailed visual walkthroughs. (you will definitely need to do that)"
		""
		"Now let's create your first machinery"
	]
	quest.6D677805996BDA93.quest_subtitle: "Welcome to Create!"
	quest.6D677805996BDA93.title: "&nHold&r &4[w]&r &nto&r &6Ponder&r &nto learn more!&r"
	quest.6D7FDA2E74748372.quest_desc: [
		"A mod inspired by Roleplaying Games, Fantasy and Supernatural, Magic and the Occult, Mythologies and Legends, with references to Thaumcraft, all of this implemented in an organic and natural way. "
		""
		"We try to make your game experience enjoyable, and you can improve your level as your equipment improves in a balanced way."
		"Enjoy squeezing everything that Forbidden can offer you [remember that we constantly try to improve your experience, we continually update the mod, to solve bugs, or add more content. Don't be surprised if you see a UFO!]."
		""
		"Above all have fun!"
	]
	quest.6D7FDA2E74748372.title: "Forbidden and Arcanus"
	quest.6D85A12754455BCC.quest_desc: [
		"The Digital Miner is the scale mining machine of Mekanism. However, this machine is like no other as it \"magically-teleports\" mined blocks to its inventory."
		""
		"The player can set the mining radius and the depth for its scanning area. The player can also opt to replace all mined blocks should the player wish to do so by keeping it fed with the desired material. The Digital Miner can be configured to mine ores only within a certain area. The Digital Miner can also be set to silk touch ores, but this results in higher power consumption. "
		""
		"Like all other Mekanism machines, the Digital Miner can automatically remove ores from its inventory for automated processing by other machines. It also takes the same upgrades as other Mekanism machines."
		""
		""
		"{@pagebreak}"
		""
		"The \"I\" icon toggle Inverse mode. Inverse mode mines everything that is not in the in the list. A practial use for this is to put Dirt, Grass, Sand, Sandstone, Gravel, Cobblestone and Stone into the ItemStack list and toggle the Inverse mode. The Digital Miner will mine everything but these common materials."
		""
		"The Silk Touch button toggles the Silk Touch mode. When mining coal, the miner will instead receive Coal Ore blocks, rather than pieces of Coal. However, this mode requires 6x the amount of energy it needs."
		""
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"The Auto-Eject button toggles the eject function. When a block is mined, the block will automatically be sent to a connected pipe, leading to a chest or to an ore processing machine. If the other end of the pipe is not attached to anything, the miner won't eject them."
		""
		"The Auto-Pull button toggles the pull function. When a block is mined, the miner will automatically collect one block from a container to replace the mined block. If the required replacement block is missing from the container, depending on the state of the block replacement requirement setting is (active for any filter or inactive for all filters), the miner will stop (active) or continue mining (inactive)."
		""
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"Not really a mode, but a feature of the filters. When a block is mined, you can choose to leave another block in its it by specifying a block in the filter. Using Auto-Pull mode with this feature is highly recommended so as to keep the digital miner inventory clear and not having to frequently worry about keeping a constant flow/supply of replacement blocks. "
	]
	quest.6DFE4E05FBAC9A3C.quest_desc: ["The Machete blade allows the breaking of web and plants in an area."]
	quest.6E34EA35B2345540.quest_desc: ["A Growth Mulch increases the growth rate of the Berry Tree that it is used on for 3 harvests. "]
	quest.6E89B7494758EE93.quest_desc: ["It collects items on the ground"]
	quest.6E8B6E30E41DD8CD.quest_desc: ["The Troll Caves lie beneath the highlands. They consist of both tunnel-style caves and vast underground chambers. Your first destination is in the underground mushroom gardens. Inside a small obsidian vault, you'll find a chest holding the troll's treasure, namely the Magic Beans. "]
	quest.6E8B6E30E41DD8CD.quest_subtitle: "Troll Caves"
	quest.6E8B6E30E41DD8CD.title: "Highlands"
	quest.6F1588945003CB8F.quest_desc: ["A recurve bow will decrease the draw time of a bow but make it do slightly decreased damage."]
	quest.6F8474F751BB6966.quest_desc: [
		"The &6Mechanical Harvester&r will harvest all mature crops it comes in contact with while moving forward. It will then either deposit the items to an inventory on the Contraption or, if no inventories are available, it will drop the items on to the ground. After harvesting the plants will be reset to their initial growth state."
		""
		"&6Mechanical Saws&r are powered through rotational force, and when placed down facing to the side they will automatically chop down wood blocks in front of them. When chopping down a tree or giant mushroom, it will automatically destroy the entire tree by only destroying the bottom-most block."
		""
		"While attached to a Contraption, the &6Mechanical Plough&r will break non-collidable blocks it comes in contact with (ex. snow layers). The Mechanical Plough will also move or launch entities and till soil blocks."
	]
	quest.6F8474F751BB6966.quest_subtitle: "Please see 'Ponder' for detailed contraptions!"
	quest.6FBA8362C7B256B5.title: "Creative Storage Cell"
	quest.6FBF5B8E8C96D914.quest_subtitle: "Hold [w] to Ponder to learn more!"
	quest.70AF63F8B601D2D0.quest_subtitle: "Defeat Legendaries"
	quest.70B9E6447E8D4B29.title: "Brass Sheet"
	quest.70D23E7FD975D726.quest_desc: ["Used to measure the amount blocks between two points."]
	quest.70D848484A23A4C2.quest_desc: [
		"The Chemical Infuser combines two gases to create another gas. The gas gauges on the left and right side of its GUI are the input tanks, and correspond to correspond with the left and right sides of the machine. The gauge in the middle is for the resulting gas, which likewise is output through the front of the machine. "
		""
		"The input and output sides can be changed in the UI of the machine. "
	]
	quest.716F4581775663B5.quest_desc: ["It pushes items to an adjacent inventory"]
	quest.71F7425B228485C4.title: "Counters"
	quest.7219C70B2CD284B6.quest_subtitle: "Heart of a Star"
	quest.722C6AF942A80684.title: "Mace"
	quest.7234FD5F79ABF6B0.quest_desc: [
		"When this treatise is near a workbench any major module made of stone will do extra damage and have better efficiency."
		""
		"Can be bought from mason villagers."
	]
	quest.723BD6F9D5FF8EA6.quest_desc: ["There are three primary stats, and a few secondary stats. In addition, the max level of the Enchanting Table is increased to 100, and the max levels of most enchantments are automatically increased."]
	quest.723BD6F9D5FF8EA6.quest_subtitle: "Apthosis Enchanting"
	quest.72691625FBEDFB1C.quest_subtitle: "Gas Transfer"
	quest.7275F30F2B0F74CC.quest_desc: [
		"The Forged Workbench, while not necessary, looks really nice with the Forge Hammer. It can be picked up with silk touch. "
		""
		"Surrounding this quest are a number of parts that can be salvaged from Ancient Bases to get unique abilities."
	]
	quest.7275F30F2B0F74CC.title: "Forged Workbench"
	quest.72D38A6E39D585B0.quest_subtitle: "Gym Challenge"
	quest.72D38A6E39D585B0.title: "Only 1 Winner on the Homestead"
	quest.7377500D0E368258.quest_subtitle: "Found a Minecolony"
	quest.7385A70C3CA6DD47.quest_desc: [
		"The Forge Hammer can be found in Ancient Bases where it can be used to create higher tier gear. A standard workbench or a forged workbench can be used with it."
		""
		"To activate the hammer it must be powered with 2 filled Thermal Cells, which are inserted on the sides with a right click. Accesories can then be added to the other two sides."
	]
	quest.7385A70C3CA6DD47.quest_subtitle: "Use a Forge Hammer to craft a module requireing tier 5+ hammering"
	quest.7385A70C3CA6DD47.title: "Forge Hammer"
	quest.74256E8E141D9EF7.quest_desc: ["Teleports your nearby pets to you. Useful for getting them out of sticky situations"]
	quest.745A812FC4D17090.quest_desc: ["Shovels, they are great at digging up the soft stuff like dirt and sand and can also be used to make paths."]
	quest.748E7791E3087456.quest_desc: [
		"* The Extractor has to be unused"
		""
		"* Unlike other artifacts found in the ruins this cannot be repaired with metal scrap"
	]
	quest.748E7791E3087456.quest_subtitle: "Replace the right head of a double headed tool with a Chtonic Extractor for a powerful harvesting tool"
	quest.7503C60927A97387.title: "Pastel Deeper Down"
	quest.75BB53030A7F350A.quest_desc: [
		"The very best Poké Ball with the ultimate level of performance. "
		""
		"With it, you will catch &lany&r wild Pokémon without fail. "
	]
	quest.75BB53030A7F350A.quest_subtitle: "Endless Possiblities Defined."
	quest.75C07080D6731239.quest_desc: [
		"The Knight Phantom can be found in the Goblin Knight Stronghold underneath Dark Forests."
		""
		""
		"Even with perks the Knight's Stronghold can be tough to find. I recommend a source of flight."
	]
	quest.75C07080D6731239.title: "The Dark Forest"
	quest.75F630520D632862.quest_subtitle: "Gondor calls for Aid"
	quest.760E7A380AFC8FB9.quest_desc: ["Unlike Bone Meal, &2Tree Fertilizer&r only needs one application to grow a tree, no matter where the tree is. Tree Fertilizer can only be used on &2Saplings.&r"]
	quest.76DA52AD0DCFDA6E.quest_desc: [
		"The &6Speedometer&r measures the speed of Rotational Force."
		""
		"When connected to a component, the speed of the rotation is shown by a hand on the face of the Speedometer. The higher the hand is, the faster the rotation. By using Engineer's Goggles, this speed is quantified with a number."
		""
		"The &6Stressometer&r is used to measure the amount of Stress on a Shaft. This stress is the \"load\" of the system."
		""
		"When connected to a component, the amount of stress in the system versus the stress capacity is shown by a hand on the face of the Stressometer. The higher the hand is, the more stress there is in the system. It can also output a Redstone Comparator signal, outputting at a strength of 15 when the system is overstressed. You can get more precise information such as current and max stress by using Engineer's Goggles."
	]
	quest.7741EAC5855D8B05.quest_desc: [
		"The &6Mechanical Press&r is a mechanical component that applies &5Pressing,&r &2Packing,&r and &6Compacting&r recipes to items below it. It is an important early-game item, as it is used to press Ingots into Sheets, which are important ingredients for higher-level components."
		""
		"&n&9Pressing&r&r"
		"By default, the &6Mechanical Press&r will apply &nPressing&r recipes to items underneath it. This can be set up in two ways:"
		""
		"- When placed &2one space above any block&r, it will process all valid items on the block when given rotational power. Items with no pressing recipe are unaffected."
		""
		"- When placed &3one space above a Mechanical Belt&r, it will automatically press incoming items, stalling the belt until each operation is done. Items with no pressing recipe are ignored."
		""
		"&n&9Packing&r&r"
		""
		"When a Mechanical Press is placed above a &1Basin,&r it will apply &nPacking&r or &nCompacting&r recipes to ingredients in the Basin. Packing and Compacting recipes are applied one at a time and cannot be applied in bulk."
		""
		"The Press will automatically process any valid recipe it detects inside the &1Basin,&r regardless if there are leftovers inside, as long as the Basin has inventory space remaining."
	]
	quest.7741EAC5855D8B05.quest_subtitle: "Pressing, Packing, and Compacting"
	quest.77957AB6B1A17FFB.title: "Ultimate Rare Candy"
	quest.77BE21B5DAA11294.quest_desc: ["Safes are harder to break shulker boxes that can be only be opened by the player who placed them."]
	quest.77CD23BD52A1F3E0.quest_desc: ["Utility blocks to the game to help you set up your gym. Most of these blocks are redstone activated and/or emit redstone signals, allowing you to tie in whatever gadgets and contraptions you want!"]
	quest.77CD23BD52A1F3E0.quest_subtitle: "Avengers Assemble"
	quest.7853F4333CEA424A.quest_subtitle: "Discover a Small Prairie House"
	quest.788795772632D09F.quest_desc: [
		"To progress further and get better hammers you will need to go exploring underground in cold biomes (Mountains, Taiga, etc.) for Ancient Bases. To help locate these bases a holosphere can be upgraded with an Eye of Ender to give it a proximity tracker of bases (they can sometimes be seen in the minimap while underground)."
		""
		"While exploring these dungeons it would be good to bring a hammer and claw tool to be able to salvage objects in the bases. When looking at blocks they will sometimes show a hammer or crowbar symbol along with a box where right clicking will do an action. A white icon means the action can happen, while red means it will not work, and yellow will have a chance to fail. Salvage will give you unique components and materials that you can use."
	]
	quest.788795772632D09F.title: "Exploration of Ancients Bases"
	quest.78E28C0AC35B8716.quest_desc: [
		"/tpa <player> - Requests teleportation to player"
		""
		"/tpahere <player> - Requests player to teleport to you"
		""
		"/tpaccept <id> - Accepts request (will have a button for it on screen)"
		""
		"/tpadeny <id> - Denies request (will have a button for it on screen)"
		""
		""
		"{@pagebreak}"
		""
		"Some commands are restricted over dimensions. &6Tempad&r is the endgame portal control."
	]
	quest.78E28C0AC35B8716.quest_subtitle: "Player to Player Transporation"
	quest.7943CB775123BE57.quest_desc: [
		"&6Chutes&r can insert or extract from inventories above or below them."
		""
		"Connected &6chutes&r will pass items along, similarly to a Mechanical Belt, though vertically. Chutes can be connected to other chutes upwards and diagonally."
	]
	quest.79D6A542A0729479.quest_desc: [
		"There are four types of Casings: "
		""
		"- &7Andesite&r Casings are mainly used in basic contraptions, "
		""
		"- &6Brass&r Casings are used in more advanced machines, "
		""
		"- &eCopper&r Casings are strictly for fluids,"
		""
		"- &8Train&r Casings for locomotive transportation."
	]
	quest.79D6A542A0729479.quest_subtitle: "Basic blocks used throughout many crafting recipes in Create, as well as for decoration and aesthetic purposes."
	quest.79F8F49311C56B61.quest_desc: ["Clipboard Integration: Right-click while shifted a Minecolonies Hut Builder block with a Create Clipboard."]
	quest.7A0A8F9479A34D76.quest_subtitle: "Modern Features are Free"
	quest.7ABE0BBE663DC8AD.quest_desc: [
		"The &6Precision Mechanism&r is used in multiple gadgets."
		""
		"&6&nSequenced Assembly&r&r"
		""
		"&6Sequenced Assembly&r starts with a base item. The item passes through or under machines like &5Deployers&r and &5Mechanical Saws&r via Depots or Mechanical Belts to create an incomplete item. The incomplete item needs to pass through the next stages of crafting and may need to repeat the whole process multiple times depending on the item being crafted."
		""
		"The sequence for &6Precision Mechanism&r needs to be repeated &nexactly&r 5 times, so you will need 5 of each item. You can always bring the &oIncomplete Precision Mechanism&r back to the start, but this process can be automated. To automate returning the Incomplete Precision Mechanism back to the start of the sequence, you can:"
		""
		"- Use a &eWeighted Ejector&r to toss it back to the start from the end of the sequence."
		""
		"- Use an &9Item Vault&r with the Brass Funnel's item filter set to only accept Incomplete Precision Mechanisms on the ending part of the sequence and an Andesite Funnel set to OUTPUT mode on the beginning part of the sequence. This method is instant item transportation."
	]
	quest.7AFE7E2E3F95D61B.title: "TR: False Swipe"
	quest.7B3274DCE7597090.title: "Bastard Blade"
	quest.7B4C7D4EFB17D209.quest_desc: ["*Only available through obtaining the scroll in dungeon loot"]
	quest.7B4C7D4EFB17D209.title: "Dreadnought Bow"
	quest.7BC94372A9C4E217.quest_desc: ["The good old fashioned slice and dicer."]
	quest.7BC94372A9C4E217.quest_subtitle: "Place a vanilla sword in a workbench and upgrade it"
	quest.7BE9BEA61F6150BB.quest_desc: [
		"&4Powered Latch&r"
		"A powered latch has two inputs (a set and reset) and one output. The side with the redstone torch is the output. The opposite side is the set line. Either of the other two sides can act as the reset line. A pulse to the set line will power the latch which will maintain a powered output until a pulse is detected on the reset line. When the output is on, any pulses to the set line will be ignored. When the output is off, any pulses to the reset line will be ignored. Both the set and reset actions are triggered on the ascending edge of the pulse."
		""
		"Continuous Signals"
		"When continuous signals are applied rather than pulses, the behavior of the powered latch becomes more complicated. If the output is off when power is applied to the set line, the output will turn on regardless of the state of the reset signal. If the set line is subsequently turned off, then the output will remain on if the reset line is unpowered but will turn off if the reset line is powered. If the output is on when power is applied to the reset line, the output will turn off regardless of the state of the set signal. If the reset line is subsequently turned off, then the output will remain off if the set line is unpowered but will turn on if the set line is powered."
		""
		"Manual Operation"
		"A powered latch can also be turned on and off manually whenever the signals to the set and reset line are the same. When they are opposite, the latch is locked in its current state and cannot be changed manually."
		""
		"Circuit Behaviors"
		"Similar to a redstone repeater, a powered latch can both power opaque blocks and can take signal inputs from opaque blocks."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"&4Redstone Link&r"
		"Redstone links transfer redstone signals across long distances, keeping their redstone signal strength. Receivers will output the strongest redstone strength received from sending links."
		""
		"To toggle the redstone link between sending and receiving a signal, hold Shift and right click it or right click with a Wrench. A redstone link in receiving mode will show a signal dish on the antenna. Assign an item or block to at least one of the two frequency slots, and the redstone link will only send or receive signals to or from links with matching frequency slots."
		""
		"The redstone link has a signal strength of a radius of 256 blocks, which does not require line-of-sight and thus can be placed underground, in a separate structure, etc. Note that the redstone link seems to have a 'default state' of OFF, and any redstone links that are actively receiving when a world is saved will briefly pulse OFF when the world is loaded again; this can cause unintended behaviors in contraptions that rely upon heavily active links."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"&4Analog Lever&r"
		"Emits a redstone signal with an adjustable strength. Right click to make it higher, shift right click to make it lower. The current signal strength can be viewed by looking at the lever while wearing Engineer's Goggles."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"&4Pulse Extender&r"
		"A pulse extender extends pulses. It emits a variable length pulse immediately after receiving a trigger signal. The output is normally off by default and emits a powered pulse when triggered."
		""
		"It can also be inverted to be normally on and emit a negative (power off) pulse by right-clicking it. Regardless of which mode it is in, the device will begin outputting a pulse immediately after detecting the ascending edge (off to on) of a redstone signal. The pulse will remain on as long as the trigger signal is on. The pulse length timer begins counting down only after the device detects a descending edge (on to off) of the trigger signal. Once the device is triggered, additional signal pulses will be ignored until the active pulse is complete."
		""
		"Pulse Length"
		"The pulse length can be changed by placing the crosshairs over the center of the device and moving the scroll wheel on the mouse. Pulse lengths can be set from 2-19 ticks, 1-59 seconds, and 1-30 minutes. The device will accept changes to the pulse length after the ascending edge trigger and before the descending edge trigger. After the descending edge trigger, the device will accept changes that shorten the pulse length but ignore changes that lengthen it."
		""
		"Circuit Behaviors"
		"Similar to a redstone repeater, a pulse extender acts as a diode transmitting a signal only in one direction. It outputs a signal strength of 15 regardless of the input strength thus behaving as a circuit extender. And it can both power and draw power from opaque blocks."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"&4Pulse Repeater&r"
		"A pulse repeater is a redstone device that emits a pulse a set delay after receiving a trigger signal. It can also be set to output a redstone signal by default and to emit a negative pulse after the time delay. Right-clicking the device toggles it between positive and negative pulse outputs. Regardless of the type of pulse selected, the device is triggered on the ascending edge of a redstone signal (off to on). Additional trigger signals will be ignored until after the pulse is complete."
		""
		"Delay Settings"
		"The delay can be changed by placing the crosshairs over the center of the device and moving the scroll wheel on the mouse. Delay times can be set from 2-19 ticks, 1-59 seconds, and 1-30 minutes. Once the device is triggered and the delay is counting down, changes to the delay time will not take effect until the currently triggered pulse is done."
		""
		"Circuit Behaviors"
		"Similar to a redstone repeater, a pulse pepeater acts as a diode transmitting a signal only in one direction. It outputs a signal strength of 15 regardless of the input strength thus behaving as a circuit extender. And it can both power and draw power from opaque blocks."
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"&4Powered Toggle Latch&r"
		"A powered toggle latch has one input and one output. The output is on the side with the redstone torch. The input is on the opposite side. When a pulse is detected on the input, the power state of the output is toggled (off to on or on to off.) The latch reacts to the ascending edge of the pulse. The latch can also be switched on or off manually regardless of the state of the input signal. Similar to a redstone repeater, a powered toggle latch can both power opaque blocks and can take signal inputs from opaque blocks."
	]
	quest.7C948A9809D7B1AD.quest_desc: [
		"A Heat Generator converts heat energy into power. The Heat Generator can generate power in both an &4active&r and a &1passive&r mode simultaneously."
		""
		""
		"{@pagebreak}"
		""
		"The &4active&r mode of generation comes from loading combustible materials into the generator. They will be burned, and the heat will be converted to power at the rate of 4 kJ/s (200 J/t). All active power fuels generate power at the same rate, but higher tier fuels will burn for a longer time, producing more total power. If a lava bucket is fed into the Heat Generator, it will consume the lava, but return the bucket."
		""
		""
		"&1Passive&r power can be generated by placing the Heat Generator adjacent to a lava source or flowing lava. For each side that is next to lava, it will generate 600 J/s (30 J/t per side). If the generator is lavalogged, it counts as an extra side. "
	]
	quest.7C948A9809D7B1AD.title: "Heat Generator"
	quest.7CA034420293B0AE.quest_subtitle: "Have 25 citizens"
	quest.7CE9E7F36D8079AB.quest_subtitle: "A Mighty Hero Deserves Rewards"
	quest.7CE9E7F36D8079AB.title: "Login 5 Weeks"
	quest.7D10898F4947456E.quest_desc: [
		"A Mega Stone is a type of item introduced in Generation VI that, if activated with a Key Stone, causes a specific Pokémon to undergo Mega Evolution. "
		""
		"There are 92 known Mega Stones, corresponding to 86 different Pokémon (one or more for every species that can Mega Evolve, except Rayquaza). "
	]
	quest.7D59CE5A434CD1DC.title: "Tour Spawn"
	quest.7D681851E0174F8E.quest_subtitle: "Items of Power"
	quest.7DB111AFF620FC85.quest_desc: [
		"&6&nFluid Pipe&r&r"
		""
		"&9Fluid Pipes&r can be adjacent without connecting if they have been made transparent with a Wrench, are encased with Copper Casing, or have a Wooden or Metal Bracket. Unlike Brackets or windowed pipes, Copper Casing can be placed on the corners of Fluid Pipes, locking the pipe in place and preventing it from connecting to more adjacent pipes."
		""
		"&9Fluid Pipes&r can only move one liquid at a time; if different liquids intersect, the pipe will clog. Each time a fluid network splits, the fluid transfer rate is split between outputs. Fluid Pipes require &5Mechanical Pumps&r to move liquid. A mechanical pump can only push fluid 15 blocks, so if you have a long pipeline, you'll need to space pumps every 15 blocks to push the fluid all the way through."
		""
		"&6&nMechanical Pump&r&r"
		""
		"Mechanical Pumps have a maximum range of 16 blocks on either side, though this does not seem to apply to pipes themselves. You may however have up to 30 pipes between pumps. Mechanical Pumps will move fluid in only one direction at a time."
		""
		"The Brown arrow symbols on the pump indicate the direction of flow. The flow direction can be changed by using a &5Wrench&r. When a wrench is used, the entire valve will appear to have rotated 180 degrees. The brown directional arrows will appear on the other side of the pump's gear."
		""
		"&6&nSmart Fluid Pipe&r&r"
		""
		"Can be used to allow only a certain liquid to pass through them. This can be set by placing a &5bucket&r or &5bottle&r of the liquid in the Filter slot on the pipe."
		""
		"&6&nFluid Valve&r&r"
		""
		"Fluid valves can be used to &4close&r or &2open&r the flow in a pipe. Fluid Valves can be switched between open and closed by providing Rotational Force to the side. This is often done with a &5Valve Handle&r or Gearshift. A set of directional arrows on the side of the valve will also rotate to indicate whether the valve is open or closed."
	]
	quest.7DB5642F2308F229.quest_desc: [
		"Customization Items : Rename your Trainers by using named Nametags on the spawners, or Re-skin them by using a named Ogrepon Mask on the spawners"
		""
		"Ogrepon naming syntax"
		""
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"| [username]                       | PLAYER | No prefix → Mojang API lookup   |"
		"| player:[username]                | PLAYER | Explicit Mojang username lookup |"
		"| uuid:[xxxx-xxxx-...]             | UUID   | Mojang API lookup by UUID       |"
		"| rct:[trainer_id]                 | RCT    | RCT trainerId prefix matching   |"
		"| data:[texture_filenaname]        | DATA   | Direct resource pack texture    |"
		"| reset / clear / none / default   | RESET  | Clears custom skin              |"
	]
	quest.7DD748993DDE40BF.quest_desc: [
		"This tier quintuples ingot yield. It uses the Rotary Condensentrator, Chemical Dissolution Chamber, Chemical Washer, Chemical Crystalizer, Chemical Oxidizer, and all machines from the previous tiers. "
		""
		""
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"    1 Silk Touch Ore + Sulfuric Acid → Chemical Dissolution Chamber → Ore Slurry"
		"    Ore Slurry + Water → Chemical Washer → Clean Ore Slurry → Chemical Crystalizer → Crystals"
		""
		""
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"You need a chain to make Hydrogen Chloride the same as Tier 3. You also need a source of Gravel/Flint/Gunpowder."
		""
		"    Gunpowder + Hydrogen Chloride → Chemical Injection Chamber → Sulfur"
		"    Sulfur → Chemical Oxidizer → Sulfur Dioxide"
		"    Sulfur Dioxide + Oxygen → Chemical Infuser → Sulfur Trioxide"
		"    Water → Rotary Condensentrator → Water Vapor"
		"    Water Vapor + Sulfur Trioxide → Chemical Infuser → Sulfuric Acid"
	]
	quest.7DD748993DDE40BF.quest_subtitle: "5x Ore Processing"
